# --- Class Definitions ---

# Class: pmdco:PMD_0080000 (acoustic quality)
# Adopted from IOF: <https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/qualities/Qualities-Physical/AcousticQuality>

AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000115 pmdco:PMD_0080000 "Akustische Qualität bezieht sich auf Eigenschaften, die mit Klang oder der Klangwissenschaft in Zusammenhang stehen, einschließlich Aspekten wie Tonhöhe, Lautstärke, Ton, Klangfarbe, Echo, Absorption oder Schallwellenausbreitung"@de)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000115 pmdco:PMD_0080000 "Acoustic quality pertains to properties related to sound or the science of sound, including aspects like pitch, volume, tone, timbre, echo, absorption, or sound wave propagation"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000116 pmdco:PMD_0080000 "Necessary and sufficient conditions for 'acoustic quality' have not yet been formalized. The term is defined as a specific subtype of 'physical quality'. Distinguishing criteria are domain-specific and depend on measurement conventions or source terminology not yet expressed as OWL restrictions."@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label pmdco:PMD_0080000 "akustische Qualität"@de)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label pmdco:PMD_0080000 "acoustic quality"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(skos:example pmdco:PMD_0080000 "The acoustic quality of a concert hall material is characterized by its absorption and reflection coefficients"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000116 pmdco:PMD_0080000 "PhysicalQuality(x) ← AcousticQuality(x)"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(pmdco:PMD_0000060 pmdco:PMD_0080000 "true"^^xsd:boolean)
SubClassOf(pmdco:PMD_0080000 obo:BFO_0000019)

# Class: pmdco:PMD_0080021 (sound reflection coefficient)
# Adopted from IOF: <https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/qualities/Qualities-Physical/SoundReflectionCoefficient>

AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label pmdco:PMD_0080021 "sound reflection coefficient"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label pmdco:PMD_0080021 "Schallreflexionsgrad"@de)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000115 pmdco:PMD_0080021 "Sound reflection coefficient quantifies the proportion of sound energy reflected by a surface"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000115 pmdco:PMD_0080021 "Schallreflexionsgrad quantifiziert den Anteil der Schallenergie, die von einer Oberfläche reflektiert wird"@de)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000116 pmdco:PMD_0080021 "Necessary and sufficient conditions for 'sound reflection coefficient' have not yet been formalized. The term is defined as a specific subtype of 'acoustic quality'. Distinguishing criteria are domain-specific and depend on measurement conventions or source terminology not yet expressed as OWL restrictions."@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000116 pmdco:PMD_0080021 "AcousticQuality(x) ← SoundReflectionCoefficient(x)"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(skos:example pmdco:PMD_0080021 "A concrete wall has a sound reflection coefficient near 0.99 at 500 Hz, acting nearly as a perfect reflector"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(pmdco:PMD_0000060 pmdco:PMD_0080021 "true"^^xsd:boolean)
SubClassOf(pmdco:PMD_0080021 pmdco:PMD_0080000)

# Class: pmdco:PMD_0080001 (electrical quality)
# Adopted from IOF: <https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/qualities/Qualities-Physical/ElectricalQuality>

AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label pmdco:PMD_0080001 "elektrische Qualität"@de)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label pmdco:PMD_0080001 "electrical quality"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000115 pmdco:PMD_0080001 "Electrical quality characterizes a material entity's behavior or state concerning electricity"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000115 pmdco:PMD_0080001 "Die elektrische Qualität charakterisiert das Verhalten oder den Zustand einer materiellen Einheit in Bezug auf Elektrizität"@de)
AnnotationAssertion(skos:example pmdco:PMD_0080001 "The semiconductivity of silicon is an electrical quality that determines its behavior in transistors"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000116 pmdco:PMD_0080001 "PhysicalQuality(x) ← ElectricalQuality(x)"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000116 pmdco:PMD_0080001 "Necessary and sufficient conditions for 'electrical quality' have not yet been formalized. The term is defined as a specific subtype of 'physical quality'. Distinguishing criteria are domain-specific and depend on measurement conventions or source terminology not yet expressed as OWL restrictions."@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(pmdco:PMD_0000060 pmdco:PMD_0080001 "true"^^xsd:boolean)
SubClassOf(pmdco:PMD_0080001 obo:BFO_0000019)

# Class: pmdco:PMD_0080022 (electric charge)
# Adopted from IOF: <https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/qualities/Qualities-Physical/ElectricCharge>

AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label pmdco:PMD_0080022 "elektrische Ladung"@de)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label pmdco:PMD_0080022 "electric charge"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000116 pmdco:PMD_0080022 "ElectricalQuality(x) ← ElectricCharge(x)"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000115 pmdco:PMD_0080022 "Electric charge refers to the physical property of matter causing it to experience a force when placed in an electromagnetic field"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000115 pmdco:PMD_0080022 "Elektrische Ladung bezieht sich auf die physikalische Eigenschaft von Materie, die dazu führt, dass sie eine Kraft erfährt, wenn sie in ein elektromagnetisches Feld gebracht wird"@de)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000116 pmdco:PMD_0080022 "Necessary and sufficient conditions for 'electric charge' have not yet been formalized. The term is defined as a specific subtype of 'electrical quality'. Distinguishing criteria are domain-specific and depend on measurement conventions or source terminology not yet expressed as OWL restrictions."@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(skos:example pmdco:PMD_0080022 "A capacitor stores 10 µC of electric charge at a voltage of 5 V"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(skos:altLabel pmdco:PMD_0080022 "elektrische Ladung"@de)
AnnotationAssertion(skos:altLabel pmdco:PMD_0080022 "electric charge"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(pmdco:PMD_0000060 pmdco:PMD_0080022 "true"^^xsd:boolean)
SubClassOf(pmdco:PMD_0080022 pmdco:PMD_0080001)

# Class: pmdco:PMD_0080023 (electric field strength)
# Adopted from IOF: <https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/qualities/Qualities-Physical/ElectricFieldStrength>

AnnotationAssertion(skos:example pmdco:PMD_0080023 "Between parallel capacitor plates separated by 1 mm at 100 V, the electric field strength is 1e5 V/m"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000116 pmdco:PMD_0080023 "Necessary and sufficient conditions for 'electric field strength' have not yet been formalized. The term is defined as a specific subtype of 'electrical quality'. Distinguishing criteria are domain-specific and depend on measurement conventions or source terminology not yet expressed as OWL restrictions. The definition is adapted from: https://www.britannica.com/science/electric-field."@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label pmdco:PMD_0080023 "elektrische Feldstärke"@de)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label pmdco:PMD_0080023 "electric field strength"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000115 pmdco:PMD_0080023 "Die Stärke oder Intensität des elektrischen Feldes bezieht sich auf die Stärke und Richtung des elektrischen Feldes an einem Punkt und ist entscheidend für die Bestimmung der Auswirkungen auf elektrische Ladungen in der Nähe dieses Punktes"@de)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000115 pmdco:PMD_0080023 "Electric field strength, or intensity, refers to the magnitude and direction of the electric field at a point, crucial for determining effects on electric charges near that point"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000116 pmdco:PMD_0080023 "ElectricalQuality(x) ← ElectricFieldStrength(x)"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000119 pmdco:PMD_0080023 <https://www.britannica.com/science/electric-field>)
AnnotationAssertion(pmdco:PMD_0000060 pmdco:PMD_0080023 "true"^^xsd:boolean)
SubClassOf(pmdco:PMD_0080023 pmdco:PMD_0080001)

# Class: pmdco:PMD_0080024 (dielectric strength)
# Adopted from IOF: <https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/qualities/Qualities-Physical/DielectricStrength>

AnnotationAssertion(skos:altLabel pmdco:PMD_0080024 "Dielektrische Festigkeit"@de)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000115 pmdco:PMD_0080024 "Durchschlagsfestigkeit ist eine elektrische Qualität eines Isoliermaterials, die die maximale elektrische Feldstärke angibt, die das Material aushalten kann, ohne einen elektrischen Durchschlag zu erleiden"@de)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000115 pmdco:PMD_0080024 "Dielectric strength is an electrical quality of an insulating material that specifies the maximum electric field intensity the material can sustain without undergoing electrical breakdown"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000116 pmdco:PMD_0080024 "Necessary and sufficient conditions for 'dielectric strength' have not yet been formalized. The term is defined as a specific subtype of 'electrical quality'. Distinguishing criteria are domain-specific and depend on measurement conventions not yet expressed as OWL restrictions."@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(skos:altLabel pmdco:PMD_0080024 "E_ds"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label pmdco:PMD_0080024 "dielectric strength"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label pmdco:PMD_0080024 "Durchschlagsfestigkeit"@de)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000116 pmdco:PMD_0080024 "ElectricalQuality(x) ← DielectricStrength(x)"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(pmdco:PMD_0000060 pmdco:PMD_0080024 "true"^^xsd:boolean)
SubClassOf(pmdco:PMD_0080024 pmdco:PMD_0080001)

# Class: pmdco:PMD_0080002 (magnetic quality)
# Adopted from IOF: <https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/qualities/Qualities-Physical/MagneticQuality>

AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label pmdco:PMD_0080002 "magnetic quality"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label pmdco:PMD_0080002 "magnetische Qualität"@de)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000116 pmdco:PMD_0080002 "PhysicalQuality(x) ← MagneticQuality(x)"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000115 pmdco:PMD_0080002 "Magnetic quality characterizes a material entity's response to external magnetic fields or its emission of magnetic fields"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000115 pmdco:PMD_0080002 "Die magnetische Qualität charakterisiert die Reaktion eines materiellen Gebildes auf äußere Magnetfelder oder die Emission von Magnetfeldern"@de)
AnnotationAssertion(skos:example pmdco:PMD_0080002 "The magnetic susceptibility of paramagnetic aluminum is a magnetic quality measured by a magnetometer"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000116 pmdco:PMD_0080002 "Necessary and sufficient conditions for 'magnetic quality' have not yet been formalized. The term is defined as a specific subtype of 'physical quality'. Distinguishing criteria are domain-specific and depend on measurement conventions or source terminology not yet expressed as OWL restrictions."@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(pmdco:PMD_0000060 pmdco:PMD_0080002 "true"^^xsd:boolean)
SubClassOf(pmdco:PMD_0080002 obo:BFO_0000019)

# Class: pmdco:PMD_0080025 (magnetic flux)
# Adopted from IOF: <https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/qualities/Qualities-Physical/MagneticFlux>

AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000115 pmdco:PMD_0080025 "Magnetic flux is the total number of magnetic field lines passing through a given area"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000115 pmdco:PMD_0080025 "Magnetischer Fluss ist die Gesamtanzahl der Magnetfeldlinien, die durch eine bestimmte Fläche verlaufen"@de)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000116 pmdco:PMD_0080025 "MagneticQuality(x) ← MagneticFlux(x)"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(skos:altLabel pmdco:PMD_0080025 "magnetischer Fluss"@de)
AnnotationAssertion(skos:altLabel pmdco:PMD_0080025 "magnetic flux"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label pmdco:PMD_0080025 "magnetischer Fluss"@de)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label pmdco:PMD_0080025 "magnetic flux"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(skos:altLabel pmdco:PMD_0080025 "magnetic field"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(skos:altLabel pmdco:PMD_0080025 "Magnetfeld"@de)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000116 pmdco:PMD_0080025 "Necessary and sufficient conditions for 'magnetic flux' have not yet been formalized. The term is defined as a specific subtype of 'magnetic quality'. Distinguishing criteria are domain-specific and depend on measurement conventions or source terminology not yet expressed as OWL restrictions."@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(skos:example pmdco:PMD_0080025 "A transformer core carries a magnetic flux of 1 mWb through its cross-section at rated voltage"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(pmdco:PMD_0000060 pmdco:PMD_0080025 "true"^^xsd:boolean)
SubClassOf(pmdco:PMD_0080025 pmdco:PMD_0080002)

# Class: pmdco:PMD_0080026 (magnetic permeability)
# Adopted from IOF: <https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/qualities/Qualities-Physical/MagneticPermeability>

AnnotationAssertion(skos:altLabel pmdco:PMD_0080026 "μ"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000115 pmdco:PMD_0080026 "Magnetic permeability is a magnetic quality of a material that quantifies its ability to support the formation of a magnetic field within itself, expressed as the ratio of magnetic flux density to the applied magnetic field intensity"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000115 pmdco:PMD_0080026 "Magnetische Permeabilität ist eine magnetische Qualität eines Materials, die seine Fähigkeit quantifiziert, ein Magnetfeld in seinem Inneren zu unterstützen, ausgedrückt als Verhältnis der magnetischen Flussdichte zur aufgebrachten magnetischen Feldstärke"@de)
AnnotationAssertion(skos:altLabel pmdco:PMD_0080026 "Permeabilität"@de)
AnnotationAssertion(skos:altLabel pmdco:PMD_0080026 "permeability"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000116 pmdco:PMD_0080026 "MagneticQuality(x) ← MagneticPermeability(x)"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label pmdco:PMD_0080026 "magnetic permeability"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label pmdco:PMD_0080026 "magnetische Permeabilität"@de)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000116 pmdco:PMD_0080026 "Necessary and sufficient conditions for 'magnetic permeability' have not yet been formalized. The term is defined as a specific subtype of 'magnetic quality'. Distinguishing criteria are domain-specific and depend on measurement conventions not yet expressed as OWL restrictions."@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(pmdco:PMD_0000060 pmdco:PMD_0080026 "true"^^xsd:boolean)
SubClassOf(pmdco:PMD_0080026 pmdco:PMD_0080002)

# Class: pmdco:PMD_0080027 (coercivity)
# Adopted from IOF: <https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/qualities/Qualities-Physical/Coercivity>

AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000116 pmdco:PMD_0080027 "MagneticQuality(x) ← Coercivity(x)"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(skos:altLabel pmdco:PMD_0080027 "coercive force"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(skos:altLabel pmdco:PMD_0080027 "coercive field"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(skos:altLabel pmdco:PMD_0080027 "Koerzitivkraft"@de)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label pmdco:PMD_0080027 "Koerzitivfeldstärke"@de)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label pmdco:PMD_0080027 "coercivity"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000115 pmdco:PMD_0080027 "Koerzitivfeldstärke ist eine magnetische Qualität eines ferromagnetischen Materials, die die Stärke des aufzubringenden Magnetfelds angibt, das erforderlich ist, um seine Magnetisierung nach vollständiger Magnetisierung auf null zu reduzieren"@de)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000115 pmdco:PMD_0080027 "Coercivity is a magnetic quality of a ferromagnetic material that specifies the magnitude of the applied magnetic field required to reduce its magnetization to zero after it has been fully magnetised"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000116 pmdco:PMD_0080027 "Necessary and sufficient conditions for 'coercivity' have not yet been formalized. The term is defined as a specific subtype of 'magnetic quality'. Distinguishing criteria are domain-specific and depend on measurement conventions not yet expressed as OWL restrictions."@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(skos:altLabel pmdco:PMD_0080027 "H_c"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(pmdco:PMD_0000060 pmdco:PMD_0080027 "true"^^xsd:boolean)
SubClassOf(pmdco:PMD_0080027 pmdco:PMD_0080002)

# Class: pmdco:PMD_0080003 (mechanical quality)
# Adopted from IOF: <https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/qualities/Qualities-Physical/MechanicalQuality>

AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label pmdco:PMD_0080003 "mechanische Qualität"@de)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label pmdco:PMD_0080003 "mechanical quality"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000116 pmdco:PMD_0080003 "Necessary and sufficient conditions for 'mechanical quality' have not yet been formalized. The term is defined as a specific subtype of 'physical quality'. Distinguishing criteria are domain-specific and depend on measurement conventions or source terminology not yet expressed as OWL restrictions."@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000116 pmdco:PMD_0080003 "PhysicalQuality(x) ← MechanicalQuality(x)"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000115 pmdco:PMD_0080003 "Mechanical quality is related to the performance of a material when enduring mechanical loads"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000115 pmdco:PMD_0080003 "Die mechanische Qualität bezieht sich auf die Leistung eines Materials, wenn es mechanischen Belastungen standhält"@de)
AnnotationAssertion(skos:example pmdco:PMD_0080003 "The fatigue strength of a connecting rod is a mechanical quality critical for engine reliability"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(pmdco:PMD_0000060 pmdco:PMD_0080003 "true"^^xsd:boolean)
SubClassOf(pmdco:PMD_0080003 obo:BFO_0000019)

# Class: pmdco:PMD_0080028 (deformation)
# Adopted from IOF: <https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/qualities/Qualities-Physical/Deformation>

AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label pmdco:PMD_0080028 "deformation"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label pmdco:PMD_0080028 "Verformung"@de)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000115 pmdco:PMD_0080028 "Unter Verformung versteht man die Änderung der Form oder Größe eines Objekts, quantifiziert als verbleibende Verschiebung von Partikeln in einem nicht starren Körper, ohne durchschnittliche Translation und Rotation"@de)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000115 pmdco:PMD_0080028 "Deformation refers to the change in shape or size of an object, quantified as the residual displacement of particles in a non-rigid body, excluding average translation and rotation"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000119 pmdco:PMD_0080028 <https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Deformation_(physics)>)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000116 pmdco:PMD_0080028 "Necessary and sufficient conditions for 'deformation' have not yet been formalized. The term is defined as a specific subtype of 'mechanical quality'. Distinguishing criteria are domain-specific and depend on measurement conventions or source terminology not yet expressed as OWL restrictions. The definition is adapted from: https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Deformation_(physics)."@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000116 pmdco:PMD_0080028 "MechanicalQuality(x) ← Deformation(x)"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(skos:example pmdco:PMD_0080028 "Under a compressive load, a foam pad undergoes 10 mm of deformation before reaching densification"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(pmdco:PMD_0000060 pmdco:PMD_0080028 "true"^^xsd:boolean)
SubClassOf(pmdco:PMD_0080028 pmdco:PMD_0080003)

# Class: pmdco:PMD_0080029 (strain)
# Adopted from IOF: <https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/qualities/Qualities-Physical/Strain>

AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000115 pmdco:PMD_0080029 "Strain is defined as relative deformation, compared to a reference position configuration"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000115 pmdco:PMD_0080029 "Dehnung ist als relative Verformung definiert, verglichen mit einer Referenzpositionskonfiguration"@de)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label pmdco:PMD_0080029 "strain"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label pmdco:PMD_0080029 "Dehnung"@de)
AnnotationAssertion(skos:example pmdco:PMD_0080029 "Under a tensile load, a polymer film exhibits a strain of 2 % before yielding"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000116 pmdco:PMD_0080029 "Deformation(x) ← Strain(x)"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000119 pmdco:PMD_0080029 <https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Strain_(mechanics)>)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000116 pmdco:PMD_0080029 "Necessary and sufficient conditions for 'strain' have not yet been formalized. The term is defined as a specific subtype of 'deformation'. Distinguishing criteria are domain-specific and depend on measurement conventions or source terminology not yet expressed as OWL restrictions. The definition is adapted from: https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Strain_(mechanics)."@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(pmdco:PMD_0000060 pmdco:PMD_0080029 "true"^^xsd:boolean)
SubClassOf(pmdco:PMD_0080029 pmdco:PMD_0080028)

# Class: pmdco:PMD_0080030 (engineering strain)
# Adopted from IOF: <https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/qualities/Qualities-Physical/EngineeringStrain>

AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000116 pmdco:PMD_0080030 "Strain(x) ← EngineeringStrain(x)"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label pmdco:PMD_0080030 "technische Dehnung"@de)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label pmdco:PMD_0080030 "engineering strain"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(skos:altLabel pmdco:PMD_0080030 "technical strain"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(skos:altLabel pmdco:PMD_0080030 "Cauchy strain"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000116 pmdco:PMD_0080030 "Necessary and sufficient conditions for 'engineering strain' have not yet been formalized. The term is defined as a specific subtype of 'strain'. Distinguishing criteria are domain-specific and depend on measurement conventions or source terminology not yet expressed as OWL restrictions. The definition is adapted from: https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Strain_(mechanics)."@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000119 pmdco:PMD_0080030 <https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Strain_(mechanics)>)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000115 pmdco:PMD_0080030 "Engineering strain, or Cauchy strain, expresses total deformation relative to the initial dimension of the material under load, reflecting elongation in axial loading"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000115 pmdco:PMD_0080030 "Die technische Dehnung oder Cauchy-Dehnung drückt die Gesamtverformung relativ zur ursprünglichen Abmessung des Materials unter Last aus und spiegelt die Dehnung bei axialer Belastung wider"@de)
AnnotationAssertion(skos:example pmdco:PMD_0080030 "A tensile specimen elongates from 50 mm to 55 mm gauge length, giving an engineering strain of 10 %"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(pmdco:PMD_0000060 pmdco:PMD_0080030 "true"^^xsd:boolean)
SubClassOf(pmdco:PMD_0080030 pmdco:PMD_0080029)

# Class: pmdco:PMD_0080031 (creep strain)
# Adopted from IOF: <https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/qualities/Qualities-Physical/CreepStrain>

AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000116 pmdco:PMD_0080031 "Necessary and sufficient conditions for 'creep strain' have not yet been formalized. The term is defined as a specific subtype of 'strain'. Distinguishing criteria are domain-specific and depend on measurement conventions or source terminology not yet expressed as OWL restrictions."@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000115 pmdco:PMD_0080031 "Eine Kriechverformung tritt auf, wenn ein Material einer konstanten Belastung über einen langen Zeitraum ausgesetzt ist"@de)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000115 pmdco:PMD_0080031 "Creep strain occurs when a material is subjected to constant stress over a long period of time"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label pmdco:PMD_0080031 "Kriechverformung"@de)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label pmdco:PMD_0080031 "creep strain"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000116 pmdco:PMD_0080031 "Strain(x) ← CreepStrain(x)"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(skos:altLabel pmdco:PMD_0080031 "Kriechverformung"@de)
AnnotationAssertion(skos:altLabel pmdco:PMD_0080031 "creep strain"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(skos:altLabel pmdco:PMD_0080031 "Kriechbeanspruchung"@de)
AnnotationAssertion(skos:altLabel pmdco:PMD_0080031 "creeping strain"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(skos:example pmdco:PMD_0080031 "A nickel alloy turbine blade accumulates 0.5 % creep strain after 10000 hours at 900 C"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(pmdco:PMD_0000060 pmdco:PMD_0080031 "true"^^xsd:boolean)
SubClassOf(pmdco:PMD_0080031 pmdco:PMD_0080029)

# Class: pmdco:PMD_0080032 (true strain)
# Adopted from IOF: <https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/qualities/Qualities-Physical/TrueStrain>

AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000115 pmdco:PMD_0080032 "True strain, or logarithmic strain, integrates incrementally over deformation; related to engineering strain as ε=ln(1+e)"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000115 pmdco:PMD_0080032 "Wahre Dehnung, auch als logarithmische Dehnung bekannt, integriert sich schrittweise über die Verformung; in Beziehung zum technischen Dehnungsmaß als ε=ln(1+e)"@de)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label pmdco:PMD_0080032 "wahre Dehnung"@de)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label pmdco:PMD_0080032 "true strain"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000116 pmdco:PMD_0080032 "Strain(x) ← TrueStrain(x)"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(skos:example pmdco:PMD_0080032 "At a cross-section reduction of 50 %, the true strain is ln(2) = 0.693"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000119 pmdco:PMD_0080032 <https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Strain_(mechanics)>)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000116 pmdco:PMD_0080032 "Necessary and sufficient conditions for 'true strain' have not yet been formalized. The term is defined as a specific subtype of 'strain'. Distinguishing criteria are domain-specific and depend on measurement conventions or source terminology not yet expressed as OWL restrictions. The definition is adapted from: https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Strain_(mechanics)."@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(skos:altLabel pmdco:PMD_0080032 "logarithmic strain"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(skos:altLabel pmdco:PMD_0080032 "Hencky strain"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(pmdco:PMD_0000060 pmdco:PMD_0080032 "true"^^xsd:boolean)
SubClassOf(pmdco:PMD_0080032 pmdco:PMD_0080029)

# Class: pmdco:PMD_0080033 (strain at break)
# Adopted from IOF: <https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/qualities/Qualities-Physical/StrainAtBreak>

AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000116 pmdco:PMD_0080033 "StrainAtBreak(x) ↔ Strain(x) ∧ ∃b∃p∃i(obo:BFO_0000040(b) ∧ MeasurementProcess(p) ∧ MeasurementInformationContentEntity(i) ∧ bearerOf(b, x) ∧ describes(i, x) ∧ isOutputOf(i, p) ∧ ∃t(TimeOfBreak(t) ∧ occupiesTemporalRegion(p, t)))"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label pmdco:PMD_0080033 "Bruchdehnung"@de)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label pmdco:PMD_0080033 "strain at break"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000115 pmdco:PMD_0080033 "Strain at break is the strain of a specimen at the moment of fracture, determined under tensile load according to applicable test standards"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000115 pmdco:PMD_0080033 "Bruchdehnung ist die Dehnung einer Probe im Moment des Bruchs, bestimmt unter Zugbelastung gemäß anwendbaren Prüfnormen"@de)
AnnotationAssertion(skos:altLabel pmdco:PMD_0080033 "elongation at break"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(skos:example pmdco:PMD_0080033 "Strain at break of a thermoplastic polyurethane specimen measured as 450% under ISO 527 test conditions."@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(pmdco:PMD_0000060 pmdco:PMD_0080033 "true"^^xsd:boolean)
SubClassOf(pmdco:PMD_0080033 pmdco:PMD_0080029)

# Class: pmdco:PMD_0080034 (elastic strain)
# Adopted from IOF: <https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/qualities/Qualities-Physical/ElasticStrain>

AnnotationAssertion(skos:example pmdco:PMD_0080034 "Steel loaded to 200 MPa exhibits an elastic strain of about 0.001, fully recovered upon unloading"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label pmdco:PMD_0080034 "elastic strain"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label pmdco:PMD_0080034 "elastische Deformation"@de)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000116 pmdco:PMD_0080034 "Necessary and sufficient conditions for 'elastic strain' have not yet been formalized. The term is defined as a specific subtype of 'strain'. Distinguishing criteria are domain-specific and depend on measurement conventions or source terminology not yet expressed as OWL restrictions. The definition is adapted from: https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Plasticity_(physics)."@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000119 pmdco:PMD_0080034 <https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Plasticity_(physics)>)
AnnotationAssertion(skos:altLabel pmdco:PMD_0080034 "elastic deformation"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(skos:altLabel pmdco:PMD_0080034 "elastische Verformung"@de)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000116 pmdco:PMD_0080034 "Strain(x) ← ElasticStrain(x)"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000115 pmdco:PMD_0080034 "Bei der elastischen Dehnung handelt es sich um eine Dehnungsqualität eines Materialgebildes, die durch eine reversible Verformung gekennzeichnet ist, die bei Wegnahme der aufgebrachten Last verschwindet"@de)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000115 pmdco:PMD_0080034 "Elastic strain is a strain quality of a material entity characterized by reversible deformation that disappears upon removal of the applied load"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(pmdco:PMD_0000060 pmdco:PMD_0080034 "true"^^xsd:boolean)
SubClassOf(pmdco:PMD_0080034 pmdco:PMD_0080029)

# Class: pmdco:PMD_0080035 (plastic strain)
# Adopted from IOF: <https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/qualities/Qualities-Physical/PlasticStrain>

AnnotationAssertion(skos:altLabel pmdco:PMD_0080035 "plastische Verformung"@de)
AnnotationAssertion(skos:altLabel pmdco:PMD_0080035 "plastic deformation"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000115 pmdco:PMD_0080035 "Plastische Deformation beschreibt die dauerhafte Verformung, die auftritt, wenn ein Material einer Belastung ausgesetzt wird, die über seine elastische Grenze hinausgeht"@de)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000115 pmdco:PMD_0080035 "Plastic strain describes permanent deformation occurring when a material is subjected to stress beyond its elastic limit"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(skos:example pmdco:PMD_0080035 "After exceeding yield strength, a steel rod undergoes 5 % plastic strain that remains after unloading"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label pmdco:PMD_0080035 "plastische Deformation"@de)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label pmdco:PMD_0080035 "plastic strain"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000116 pmdco:PMD_0080035 "Necessary and sufficient conditions for 'plastic strain' have not yet been formalized. The term is defined as a specific subtype of 'strain'. Distinguishing criteria are domain-specific and depend on measurement conventions or source terminology not yet expressed as OWL restrictions. The definition is adapted from: https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Plasticity_(physics)."@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000116 pmdco:PMD_0080035 "Strain(x) ← PlasticStrain(x)"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000119 pmdco:PMD_0080035 <https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Plasticity_(physics)>)
AnnotationAssertion(pmdco:PMD_0000060 pmdco:PMD_0080035 "true"^^xsd:boolean)
SubClassOf(pmdco:PMD_0080035 pmdco:PMD_0080029)

# Class: pmdco:PMD_0080004 (optical quality)
# Adopted from IOF: <https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/qualities/Qualities-Physical/OpticalQuality>

AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000116 pmdco:PMD_0080004 "PhysicalQuality(x) ← OpticalQuality(x)"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(skos:example pmdco:PMD_0080004 "The optical quality of a mirror is assessed by its surface flatness and reflectance uniformity"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000116 pmdco:PMD_0080004 "Necessary and sufficient conditions for 'optical quality' have not yet been formalized. The term is defined as a specific subtype of 'physical quality'. Distinguishing criteria are domain-specific and depend on measurement conventions or source terminology not yet expressed as OWL restrictions."@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label pmdco:PMD_0080004 "optische Qualität"@de)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label pmdco:PMD_0080004 "optical quality"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000115 pmdco:PMD_0080004 "Optical quality characterizes the interaction results of material entities with light emissions or their generation of light emissions"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000115 pmdco:PMD_0080004 "Die optische Qualität charakterisiert die Interaktionsergebnisse materieller Einheiten mit Lichtemissionen oder deren Erzeugung von Lichtemissionen"@de)
AnnotationAssertion(pmdco:PMD_0000060 pmdco:PMD_0080004 "true"^^xsd:boolean)
SubClassOf(pmdco:PMD_0080004 obo:BFO_0000019)

# Class: pmdco:PMD_0080036 (luminous intensity)
# Adopted from IOF: <https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/qualities/Qualities-Physical/LuminousIntensity>

AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label pmdco:PMD_0080036 "Lichtstärke in cd gemessen"@de)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label pmdco:PMD_0080036 "luminous intensity"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000116 pmdco:PMD_0080036 "OpticalQuality(x) ← LuminousIntensity(x)"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000115 pmdco:PMD_0080036 "Luminous intensity quantifies the visible light emitted per unit solid angle in a particular direction from a source, measured in candela (cd)"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000115 pmdco:PMD_0080036 "Lichtstärke ist die Menge des sichtbaren Lichts, das pro Einheitswinkel in eine bestimmte Richtung von einer Quelle abgestrahlt wird, gemessen in Candela (cd)"@de)
AnnotationAssertion(skos:altLabel pmdco:PMD_0080036 "Leuchtintensität"@de)
AnnotationAssertion(skos:altLabel pmdco:PMD_0080036 "luminous intensity"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(skos:example pmdco:PMD_0080036 "A standard LED lamp emits a luminous intensity of 800 cd in the forward direction"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(skos:altLabel pmdco:PMD_0080036 "Lichtintensität"@de)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000116 pmdco:PMD_0080036 "Necessary and sufficient conditions for 'luminous intensity' have not yet been formalized. The term is defined as a specific subtype of 'optical quality'. Distinguishing criteria are domain-specific and depend on measurement conventions or source terminology not yet expressed as OWL restrictions."@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(pmdco:PMD_0000060 pmdco:PMD_0080036 "true"^^xsd:boolean)
SubClassOf(pmdco:PMD_0080036 pmdco:PMD_0080004)

# Class: pmdco:PMD_0080037 (exposure)
# Adopted from IOF: <https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/qualities/Qualities-Physical/Exposure>

AnnotationAssertion(skos:example pmdco:PMD_0080037 "A worker is exposed to a UV radiation exposure of 30 J/m2 during outdoor operations"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label pmdco:PMD_0080037 "exposure"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label pmdco:PMD_0080037 "Belichtungszeit"@de)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000119 pmdco:PMD_0080037 <https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Exposure_(photography)>)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000115 pmdco:PMD_0080037 "Unter Belichtung versteht man in der Fotografie die Lichtmenge pro Flächeneinheit, die den Film oder Sensor erreicht, bestimmt durch Verschlusszeit, Blendenzahl des Objektivs und Helligkeit der Szene"@de)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000115 pmdco:PMD_0080037 "Exposure in photography refers to the amount of light per unit area reaching film or sensor, determined by shutter speed, lens F-number, and scene luminance"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000116 pmdco:PMD_0080037 "OpticalQuality(x) ← Exposure(x)"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000116 pmdco:PMD_0080037 "Necessary and sufficient conditions for 'exposure' have not yet been formalized. The term is defined as a specific subtype of 'optical quality'. Distinguishing criteria are domain-specific and depend on measurement conventions or source terminology not yet expressed as OWL restrictions. The definition is adapted from: https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Exposure_(photography)."@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(pmdco:PMD_0000060 pmdco:PMD_0080037 "true"^^xsd:boolean)
SubClassOf(pmdco:PMD_0080037 pmdco:PMD_0080004)

# Class: pmdco:PMD_0080005 (thermo dynamic quality)
# Adopted from IOF: <https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/qualities/Qualities-Physical/ThermoDynamicQuality>

AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label pmdco:PMD_0080005 "thermodynamische Qualität"@de)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label pmdco:PMD_0080005 "thermo dynamic quality"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000115 pmdco:PMD_0080005 "Thermo dynamic quality characterizes a material entity's behavior or state in relation to thermal heating or cooling"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000115 pmdco:PMD_0080005 "Thermodynamische Qualität beschreibt das Verhalten oder den Zustand eines materiellen Wesens in Bezug auf thermische Erwärmung oder Kühlung"@de)
AnnotationAssertion(skos:example pmdco:PMD_0080005 "The melting point of iron at 1538 C is a thermo dynamic quality governing its processing in a blast furnace"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000116 pmdco:PMD_0080005 "PhysicalQuality(x) ← ThermoDynamicQuality(x)"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000116 pmdco:PMD_0080005 "Necessary and sufficient conditions for 'thermo dynamic quality' have not yet been formalized. The term is defined as a specific subtype of 'physical quality'. Distinguishing criteria are domain-specific and depend on measurement conventions or source terminology not yet expressed as OWL restrictions."@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(pmdco:PMD_0000060 pmdco:PMD_0080005 "true"^^xsd:boolean)
SubClassOf(pmdco:PMD_0080005 obo:BFO_0000019)

# Class: pmdco:PMD_0080038 (Curie temperature)
# Adopted from IOF: <https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/qualities/Qualities-Physical/CurieTemperature>

AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000115 pmdco:PMD_0080038 "Curie-Temperatur ist eine thermodynamische Qualität eines ferromagnetischen Materials, die die Temperatur angibt, oberhalb derer das Material seine permanente magnetische Ordnung verliert und paramagnetisch wird"@de)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000115 pmdco:PMD_0080038 "Curie temperature is a thermodynamic quality of a ferromagnetic material that specifies the temperature above which it loses its permanent magnetic ordering and becomes paramagnetic"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(skos:altLabel pmdco:PMD_0080038 "Curie-Punkt"@de)
AnnotationAssertion(skos:altLabel pmdco:PMD_0080038 "Curie point"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000116 pmdco:PMD_0080038 "ThermoDynamicQuality(x) ← CurieTemperature(x)"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000116 pmdco:PMD_0080038 "Necessary and sufficient conditions for 'Curie temperature' have not yet been formalized. The term is defined as a specific subtype of 'thermo dynamic quality'. Distinguishing criteria are domain-specific and depend on measurement conventions not yet expressed as OWL restrictions."@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(skos:altLabel pmdco:PMD_0080038 "T_C"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label pmdco:PMD_0080038 "Curie-Temperatur"@de)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label pmdco:PMD_0080038 "Curie temperature"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(pmdco:PMD_0000060 pmdco:PMD_0080038 "true"^^xsd:boolean)
SubClassOf(pmdco:PMD_0080038 pmdco:PMD_0080005)

# Class: pmdco:PMD_0080039 (specific heat capacity)
# Adopted from IOF: <https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/qualities/Qualities-Physical/SpecificHeatCapacity>

AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label pmdco:PMD_0080039 "spezifische Wärmekapazität"@de)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label pmdco:PMD_0080039 "specific heat capacity"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(skos:example pmdco:PMD_0080039 "Water has a specific heat capacity of 4182 J/(kg·K), making it an effective coolant"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000115 pmdco:PMD_0080039 "Spezifische Wärmekapazität ist die Wärmekapazität einer Probe geteilt durch ihre Masse und repräsentiert die erforderliche Wärme, um die Temperatur um eine Einheit zu erhöhen"@de)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000115 pmdco:PMD_0080039 "Specific heat capacity is the heat capacity of a sample divided by its mass, representing the heat required to raise temperature by one unit"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000116 pmdco:PMD_0080039 "ThermoDynamicQuality(x) ← SpecificHeatCapacity(x)"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000116 pmdco:PMD_0080039 "Necessary and sufficient conditions for 'specific heat capacity' have not yet been formalized. The term is defined as a specific subtype of 'thermo dynamic quality'. Distinguishing criteria are domain-specific and depend on measurement conventions or source terminology not yet expressed as OWL restrictions."@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(pmdco:PMD_0000060 pmdco:PMD_0080039 "true"^^xsd:boolean)
SubClassOf(pmdco:PMD_0080039 pmdco:PMD_0080005)

# Class: pmdco:PMD_0080040 (eutectic point)
# Adopted from IOF: <https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/qualities/Qualities-Physical/EutecticPoint>

AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000116 pmdco:PMD_0080040 "ThermoDynamicQuality(x) ← EutecticPoint(x)"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label pmdco:PMD_0080040 "eutektischer Punkt"@de)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label pmdco:PMD_0080040 "eutectic point"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000115 pmdco:PMD_0080040 "Eutectic point is a thermodynamic quality of a multi-component material system that specifies the composition and temperature at which all components simultaneously solidify from a liquid mixture at the lowest possible melting temperature"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000115 pmdco:PMD_0080040 "Eutektischer Punkt ist eine thermodynamische Qualität eines Mehrkomponentenmaterialsystems, die die Zusammensetzung und Temperatur angibt, bei der alle Komponenten gleichzeitig aus einer flüssigen Mischung bei der niedrigstmöglichen Schmelztemperatur erstarren"@de)
AnnotationAssertion(skos:altLabel pmdco:PMD_0080040 "eutektische Temperatur"@de)
AnnotationAssertion(skos:altLabel pmdco:PMD_0080040 "eutectic temperature"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000116 pmdco:PMD_0080040 "Necessary and sufficient conditions for 'eutectic point' have not yet been formalized. The term is defined as a specific subtype of 'thermo dynamic quality'. Distinguishing criteria are domain-specific and depend on measurement conventions not yet expressed as OWL restrictions."@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(pmdco:PMD_0000060 pmdco:PMD_0080040 "true"^^xsd:boolean)
SubClassOf(pmdco:PMD_0080040 pmdco:PMD_0080005)

# Class: pmdco:PMD_0080041 (critical pressure)
# Adopted from IOF: <https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/qualities/Qualities-Physical/CriticalPressure>

AnnotationAssertion(skos:altLabel pmdco:PMD_0080041 "p_c"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label pmdco:PMD_0080041 "critical pressure"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label pmdco:PMD_0080041 "kritischer Druck"@de)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000116 pmdco:PMD_0080041 "Necessary and sufficient conditions for 'critical pressure' have not yet been formalized. The term is defined as a specific subtype of 'thermo dynamic quality'. Distinguishing criteria are domain-specific and depend on measurement conventions not yet expressed as OWL restrictions."@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000116 pmdco:PMD_0080041 "ThermoDynamicQuality(x) ← CriticalPressure(x)"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000115 pmdco:PMD_0080041 "Critical pressure is a thermodynamic quality of a pure substance that specifies the minimum pressure required to liquefy the substance at its critical temperature"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000115 pmdco:PMD_0080041 "Kritischer Druck ist eine thermodynamische Qualität einer reinen Substanz, die den Mindestdruck angibt, der erforderlich ist, um die Substanz bei ihrer kritischen Temperatur zu verflüssigen"@de)
AnnotationAssertion(pmdco:PMD_0000060 pmdco:PMD_0080041 "true"^^xsd:boolean)
SubClassOf(pmdco:PMD_0080041 pmdco:PMD_0080005)

# Class: pmdco:PMD_0080042 (critical temperature)
# Adopted from IOF: <https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/qualities/Qualities-Physical/CriticalTemperature>

AnnotationAssertion(skos:altLabel pmdco:PMD_0080042 "T_c"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000115 pmdco:PMD_0080042 "Kritische Temperatur ist eine thermodynamische Qualität einer reinen Substanz, die die Temperatur angibt, oberhalb derer die Substanz unabhängig vom aufgebrachten Druck nicht als Flüssigkeit existieren kann"@de)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000115 pmdco:PMD_0080042 "Critical temperature is a thermodynamic quality of a pure substance that specifies the temperature above which the substance cannot exist as a liquid regardless of applied pressure"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label pmdco:PMD_0080042 "critical temperature"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label pmdco:PMD_0080042 "kritische Temperatur"@de)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000116 pmdco:PMD_0080042 "Necessary and sufficient conditions for 'critical temperature' have not yet been formalized. The term is defined as a specific subtype of 'thermo dynamic quality'. Distinguishing criteria are domain-specific and depend on measurement conventions not yet expressed as OWL restrictions."@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000116 pmdco:PMD_0080042 "ThermoDynamicQuality(x) ← CriticalTemperature(x)"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(pmdco:PMD_0000060 pmdco:PMD_0080042 "true"^^xsd:boolean)
SubClassOf(pmdco:PMD_0080042 pmdco:PMD_0080005)

# Class: pmdco:PMD_0080043 (temperature)
# Adopted from IOF: <https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/qualities/Qualities-Physical/Temperature>

AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000119 pmdco:PMD_0080043 <https://www.merriam-webster.com/dictionary/temperature>)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000116 pmdco:PMD_0080043 "Necessary and sufficient conditions for 'temperature' have not yet been formalized. The term is defined as a specific subtype of 'thermo dynamic quality'. Distinguishing criteria are domain-specific and depend on measurement conventions or source terminology not yet expressed as OWL restrictions. The definition is adapted from: https://www.merriam-webster.com/dictionary/temperature."@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000115 pmdco:PMD_0080043 "Temperatur beschreibt den Grad der Hitze oder Kälte, gemessen auf einer bestimmten Skala"@de)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000115 pmdco:PMD_0080043 "Temperature characterizes the degree of hotness or coldness measured on a definite scale"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label pmdco:PMD_0080043 "Temperatur"@de)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label pmdco:PMD_0080043 "temperature"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000116 pmdco:PMD_0080043 "ThermoDynamicQuality(x) ← Temperature(x)"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(skos:example pmdco:PMD_0080043 "The cure temperature of an epoxy adhesive is 120 C for one hour under pressure"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(pmdco:PMD_0000060 pmdco:PMD_0080043 "true"^^xsd:boolean)
SubClassOf(pmdco:PMD_0080043 pmdco:PMD_0080005)

# Class: pmdco:PMD_0080044 (aging temperature)
# Adopted from IOF: <https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/qualities/Qualities-Physical/AgingTemperature>

AnnotationAssertion(skos:example pmdco:PMD_0080044 "Al-Cu alloys are artificially aged at 175 C to precipitate strengthening phases"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000115 pmdco:PMD_0080044 "Aging temperature refers to variable temperature during an aging process depending on the desired deposition formations"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000115 pmdco:PMD_0080044 "Unter Alterungstemperatur versteht man die variable Temperatur während eines Alterungsprozesses in Abhängigkeit von der gewünschten Ablagerungsbildung"@de)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label pmdco:PMD_0080044 "Alterungstemperatur"@de)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label pmdco:PMD_0080044 "aging temperature"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000116 pmdco:PMD_0080044 "Temperature(x) ← AgingTemperature(x)"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000116 pmdco:PMD_0080044 "Necessary and sufficient conditions for 'aging temperature' have not yet been formalized. The term is defined as a specific subtype of 'temperature'. Distinguishing criteria are domain-specific and depend on measurement conventions or source terminology not yet expressed as OWL restrictions."@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(pmdco:PMD_0000060 pmdco:PMD_0080044 "true"^^xsd:boolean)
SubClassOf(pmdco:PMD_0080044 pmdco:PMD_0080043)

# Class: pmdco:PMD_0080045 (environmental temperature)
# Adopted from IOF: <https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/qualities/Qualities-Physical/EnvironmentalTemperature>

AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label pmdco:PMD_0080045 "environmental temperature"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label pmdco:PMD_0080045 "Umgebungstemperatur"@de)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000116 pmdco:PMD_0080045 "Temperature(x) ← EnvironmentalTemperature(x)"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000116 pmdco:PMD_0080045 "Necessary and sufficient conditions for 'environmental temperature' have not yet been formalized. The term is defined as a specific subtype of 'temperature'. Distinguishing criteria are domain-specific and depend on measurement conventions or source terminology not yet expressed as OWL restrictions."@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000115 pmdco:PMD_0080045 "Umgebungstemperatur ist die Eigenschaft, die die beobachtete Temperatur in der Umgebung eines betrachteten materiellen Objekts beschreibt. Dazu gehören Raumtemperatur und die in Prüfkammern gemessenen Temperaturen"@de)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000115 pmdco:PMD_0080045 "Environmental temperature describes the observed temperature surrounding a tangible object, including room temperature and temperatures measured in test chambers"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(skos:example pmdco:PMD_0080045 "A circuit board operates at an environmental temperature of 85 C in a high-reliability application"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(pmdco:PMD_0000060 pmdco:PMD_0080045 "true"^^xsd:boolean)
SubClassOf(pmdco:PMD_0080045 pmdco:PMD_0080043)

# Class: pmdco:PMD_0080046 (vapor pressure)
# Adopted from IOF: <https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/qualities/Qualities-Physical/VaporPressure>

AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000116 pmdco:PMD_0080046 "ThermoDynamicQuality(x) ← VaporPressure(x)"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000116 pmdco:PMD_0080046 "Necessary and sufficient conditions for 'vapor pressure' have not yet been formalized. The term is defined as a specific subtype of 'thermo dynamic quality'. Distinguishing criteria are domain-specific and depend on measurement conventions not yet expressed as OWL restrictions."@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label pmdco:PMD_0080046 "Dampfdruck"@de)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label pmdco:PMD_0080046 "vapor pressure"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000115 pmdco:PMD_0080046 "Vapor pressure is a thermodynamic quality of a substance that specifies the pressure exerted by its vapor when in thermodynamic equilibrium with its condensed phase at a given temperature"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000115 pmdco:PMD_0080046 "Dampfdruck ist eine thermodynamische Qualität eines Stoffes, die den Druck angibt, den sein Dampf ausübt, wenn er sich bei einer gegebenen Temperatur im thermodynamischen Gleichgewicht mit seiner kondensierten Phase befindet"@de)
AnnotationAssertion(skos:altLabel pmdco:PMD_0080046 "p*"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(pmdco:PMD_0000060 pmdco:PMD_0080046 "true"^^xsd:boolean)
SubClassOf(pmdco:PMD_0080046 pmdco:PMD_0080005)

# Class: pmdco:PMD_0080047 (flash point)
# Adopted from IOF: <https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/qualities/Qualities-Physical/FlashPoint>

AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000116 pmdco:PMD_0080047 "Necessary and sufficient conditions for 'flash point' have not yet been formalized. The term is defined as a specific subtype of 'thermo dynamic quality'. Distinguishing criteria are domain-specific and depend on measurement conventions not yet expressed as OWL restrictions."@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000115 pmdco:PMD_0080047 "Flammpunkt ist eine thermodynamische Qualität eines flüchtigen Materials, die die niedrigste Temperatur angibt, bei der sein Dampf an der Materialoberfläche ein zündfähiges Gemisch mit Luft bildet"@de)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000115 pmdco:PMD_0080047 "Flash point is a thermodynamic quality of a volatile material that specifies the lowest temperature at which its vapour forms an ignitable mixture with air near the surface of the material"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label pmdco:PMD_0080047 "flash point"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label pmdco:PMD_0080047 "Flammpunkt"@de)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000116 pmdco:PMD_0080047 "ThermoDynamicQuality(x) ← FlashPoint(x)"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(pmdco:PMD_0000060 pmdco:PMD_0080047 "true"^^xsd:boolean)
SubClassOf(pmdco:PMD_0080047 pmdco:PMD_0080005)

# Class: pmdco:PMD_0080048 (ductile-brittle transition temperature)
# Adopted from IOF: <https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/qualities/Qualities-Physical/DuctileBrittleTransitionTemperature>

AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label pmdco:PMD_0080048 "ductile-brittle transition temperature"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label pmdco:PMD_0080048 "Duktil-Spröd-Übergangstemperatur"@de)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000116 pmdco:PMD_0080048 "Necessary and sufficient conditions for 'ductile-brittle transition temperature' have not yet been formalized. The term is defined as a specific subtype of 'thermo dynamic quality'. Distinguishing criteria are domain-specific and depend on measurement conventions not yet expressed as OWL restrictions."@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000116 pmdco:PMD_0080048 "ThermoDynamicQuality(x) ← DuctileBrittleTransitionTemperature(x)"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(skos:altLabel pmdco:PMD_0080048 "nil ductility transition temperature"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(skos:altLabel pmdco:PMD_0080048 "Nullduktilitäts-Übergangstemperatur"@de)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000115 pmdco:PMD_0080048 "Duktil-Spröd-Übergangstemperatur ist eine thermodynamische Qualität eines Materials, die die Temperatur angibt, unterhalb derer das Material unter Schlagbelastung ein sprödes Bruchverhalten anstelle einer duktilen Verformung zeigt"@de)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000115 pmdco:PMD_0080048 "Ductile-brittle transition temperature is a thermodynamic quality of a material that specifies the temperature below which the material exhibits brittle fracture behaviour rather than ductile deformation under impact loading"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(skos:altLabel pmdco:PMD_0080048 "T_DBTT"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(pmdco:PMD_0000060 pmdco:PMD_0080048 "true"^^xsd:boolean)
SubClassOf(pmdco:PMD_0080048 pmdco:PMD_0080005)

# Class: pmdco:PMD_0080049 (glass transition temperature)
# Adopted from IOF: <https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/qualities/Qualities-Physical/GlassTransitionTemperature>

AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000115 pmdco:PMD_0080049 "Glass transition temperature is a ductile-brittle transition temperature of an amorphous or semi-crystalline material that specifies the temperature at which the material transitions from a hard, glassy state to a soft, rubbery state upon heating"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000115 pmdco:PMD_0080049 "Glasübergangstemperatur ist eine Duktil-Spröd-Übergangstemperatur eines amorphen oder teilkristallinen Materials, die die Temperatur beschreibt, bei der das Material beim Erwärmen von einem harten, glasartigen in einen weichen, gummiartigen Zustand übergeht"@de)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label pmdco:PMD_0080049 "Glasübergangstemperatur"@de)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label pmdco:PMD_0080049 "glass transition temperature"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000119 pmdco:PMD_0080049 <https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Glass_transition>)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000116 pmdco:PMD_0080049 "DuctileBrittleTransitionTemperature(x) ← GlassTransitionTemperature(x)"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000116 pmdco:PMD_0080049 "Necessary and sufficient conditions for 'glass transition temperature' have not yet been formalized. The term is defined as a specific subtype of 'ductile-brittle transition temperature' specific to amorphous and semi-crystalline materials. Distinguishing criteria are domain-specific and depend on measurement conventions or source terminology not yet expressed as OWL restrictions. The definition is adapted from: https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Glass_transition."@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(skos:altLabel pmdco:PMD_0080049 "Tg"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(skos:example pmdco:PMD_0080049 "Glass transition temperature of polycarbonate measured at approximately 147 °C, above which the material softens and loses rigidity, determined according to ISO 11357-2."@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(pmdco:PMD_0000060 pmdco:PMD_0080049 "true"^^xsd:boolean)
SubClassOf(pmdco:PMD_0080049 pmdco:PMD_0080048)

# Class: pmdco:PMD_0080050 (entropy)
# Adopted from IOF: <https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/qualities/Qualities-Physical/Entropy>

AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000116 pmdco:PMD_0080050 "Energy(x) ← Entropy(x)"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(skos:example pmdco:PMD_0080050 "Melting of ice at 0 C involves an entropy increase of 22 J/(mol·K), driving the phase transition"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000115 pmdco:PMD_0080050 "Entropy measures the thermal energy per unit temperature unavailable for work in a system, indicating molecular disorder or randomness"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000115 pmdco:PMD_0080050 "Die Entropie misst die Wärmeenergie pro Temperatureinheit, die für die Arbeit in einem System nicht zur Verfügung steht und auf molekulare Unordnung oder Zufälligkeit hinweist"@de)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000116 pmdco:PMD_0080050 "Necessary and sufficient conditions for 'entropy' have not yet been formalized. The term is defined as a specific subtype of 'energy'. Distinguishing criteria are domain-specific and depend on measurement conventions or source terminology not yet expressed as OWL restrictions. The definition is adapted from: https://www.britannica.com/science/entropy-physics."@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label pmdco:PMD_0080050 "entropy"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label pmdco:PMD_0080050 "Entropie"@de)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000119 pmdco:PMD_0080050 <https://www.britannica.com/science/entropy-physics>)
AnnotationAssertion(pmdco:PMD_0000060 pmdco:PMD_0080050 "true"^^xsd:boolean)
SubClassOf(pmdco:PMD_0080050 pmdco:PMD_0020142)

# Class: pmdco:PMD_0080051 (surface energy)
# Adopted from IOF: <https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/qualities/Qualities-Physical/SurfaceEnergy>

AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label pmdco:PMD_0080051 "Oberflächenenergie"@de)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label pmdco:PMD_0080051 "surface energy"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(skos:altLabel pmdco:PMD_0080051 "surface free energy"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(skos:altLabel pmdco:PMD_0080051 "freie Oberflächenenergie"@de)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000115 pmdco:PMD_0080051 "Surface energy is an energy quality of a material that quantifies the excess energy at its surface relative to the bulk, arising from unsatisfied molecular bonds at the interface"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000115 pmdco:PMD_0080051 "Oberflächenenergie ist eine Energiequalität eines Materials, die die überschüssige Energie an seiner Oberfläche im Vergleich zum Volumen quantifiziert, die durch nicht abgesättigte molekulare Bindungen an der Grenzfläche entsteht"@de)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000116 pmdco:PMD_0080051 "Energy(x) ← SurfaceEnergy(x)"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(skos:altLabel pmdco:PMD_0080051 "γ"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000116 pmdco:PMD_0080051 "Necessary and sufficient conditions for 'surface energy' have not yet been formalized. The term is defined as a specific subtype of 'energy'. Distinguishing criteria are domain-specific and depend on measurement conventions not yet expressed as OWL restrictions."@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(pmdco:PMD_0000060 pmdco:PMD_0080051 "true"^^xsd:boolean)
SubClassOf(pmdco:PMD_0080051 pmdco:PMD_0020142)

# Class: pmdco:PMD_0080052 (enthalpy)
# Adopted from IOF: <https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/qualities/Qualities-Physical/Enthalpy>

AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label pmdco:PMD_0080052 "enthalpy"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label pmdco:PMD_0080052 "Enthalpie"@de)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000115 pmdco:PMD_0080052 "Die als H bezeichnete Enthalpie stellt die Summe der inneren Energie und das Produkt aus Druck und Volumen in einem thermodynamischen System dar und ist für Energieberechnungen von entscheidender Bedeutung"@de)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000115 pmdco:PMD_0080052 "Enthalpy, denoted as H, represents the sum of internal energy and the product of pressure and volume in a thermodynamic system, crucial for energy calculations"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000119 pmdco:PMD_0080052 <https://www.britannica.com/science/enthalpy>)
AnnotationAssertion(skos:example pmdco:PMD_0080052 "The enthalpy of fusion of aluminum is 397 J/g, energy required to melt it at its melting point"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000116 pmdco:PMD_0080052 "Energy(x) ← Enthalpy(x)"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000116 pmdco:PMD_0080052 "Necessary and sufficient conditions for 'enthalpy' have not yet been formalized. The term is defined as a specific subtype of 'energy'. Distinguishing criteria are domain-specific and depend on measurement conventions or source terminology not yet expressed as OWL restrictions. The definition is adapted from: https://www.britannica.com/science/enthalpy."@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(pmdco:PMD_0000060 pmdco:PMD_0080052 "true"^^xsd:boolean)
SubClassOf(pmdco:PMD_0080052 pmdco:PMD_0020142)

# Class: pmdco:PMD_0080053 (heat of fusion)
# Adopted from IOF: <https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/qualities/Qualities-Physical/HeatOfFusion>

AnnotationAssertion(skos:altLabel pmdco:PMD_0080053 "latent heat of melting"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(skos:altLabel pmdco:PMD_0080053 "enthalpy of fusion"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(skos:altLabel pmdco:PMD_0080053 "Schmelzwärme"@de)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000116 pmdco:PMD_0080053 "Enthalpy(x) ← HeatOfFusion(x)"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label pmdco:PMD_0080053 "Schmelzenthalpie"@de)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label pmdco:PMD_0080053 "heat of fusion"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000115 pmdco:PMD_0080053 "Schmelzenthalpie ist eine Enthalpiequalität eines Stoffes, die die thermische Energie angibt, die benötigt wird, um eine Masseneinheit bei konstanter Temperatur und konstantem Druck von der festen in die flüssige Phase umzuwandeln"@de)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000115 pmdco:PMD_0080053 "Heat of fusion is an enthalpy quality of a substance that specifies the amount of thermal energy required to convert a unit mass from solid to liquid phase at constant temperature and pressure"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(skos:altLabel pmdco:PMD_0080053 "ΔH_fus"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000116 pmdco:PMD_0080053 "Necessary and sufficient conditions for 'heat of fusion' have not yet been formalized. The term is defined as a specific subtype of 'enthalpy'. Distinguishing criteria are domain-specific and depend on measurement conventions not yet expressed as OWL restrictions."@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(pmdco:PMD_0000060 pmdco:PMD_0080053 "true"^^xsd:boolean)
SubClassOf(pmdco:PMD_0080053 pmdco:PMD_0080052)

# Class: pmdco:PMD_0080054 (heat of vaporization)
# Adopted from IOF: <https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/qualities/Qualities-Physical/HeatOfVaporization>

AnnotationAssertion(skos:altLabel pmdco:PMD_0080054 "ΔH_vap"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000116 pmdco:PMD_0080054 "Enthalpy(x) ← HeatOfVaporization(x)"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000115 pmdco:PMD_0080054 "Verdampfungsenthalpie ist eine Enthalpiequalität eines Stoffes, die die thermische Energie angibt, die benötigt wird, um eine Masseneinheit bei konstanter Temperatur und konstantem Druck von der flüssigen in die gasförmige Phase umzuwandeln"@de)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000115 pmdco:PMD_0080054 "Heat of vaporization is an enthalpy quality of a substance that specifies the amount of thermal energy required to convert a unit mass from liquid to vapour phase at constant temperature and pressure"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label pmdco:PMD_0080054 "Verdampfungsenthalpie"@de)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label pmdco:PMD_0080054 "heat of vaporization"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(skos:altLabel pmdco:PMD_0080054 "enthalpy of vaporization"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(skos:altLabel pmdco:PMD_0080054 "latent heat of vaporization"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(skos:altLabel pmdco:PMD_0080054 "Verdampfungswärme"@de)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000116 pmdco:PMD_0080054 "Necessary and sufficient conditions for 'heat of vaporization' have not yet been formalized. The term is defined as a specific subtype of 'enthalpy'. Distinguishing criteria are domain-specific and depend on measurement conventions not yet expressed as OWL restrictions."@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(pmdco:PMD_0000060 pmdco:PMD_0080054 "true"^^xsd:boolean)
SubClassOf(pmdco:PMD_0080054 pmdco:PMD_0080052)

# Class: pmdco:PMD_0080055 (auto-ignition temperature)
# Adopted from IOF: <https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/qualities/Qualities-Physical/AutoIgnitionTemperature>

AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label pmdco:PMD_0080055 "auto-ignition temperature"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label pmdco:PMD_0080055 "Selbstzündungstemperatur"@de)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000116 pmdco:PMD_0080055 "Necessary and sufficient conditions for 'auto-ignition temperature' have not yet been formalized. The term is defined as a specific subtype of 'thermo dynamic quality'. Distinguishing criteria are domain-specific and depend on measurement conventions not yet expressed as OWL restrictions."@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000115 pmdco:PMD_0080055 "Selbstzündungstemperatur ist eine thermodynamische Qualität eines Stoffes, die die niedrigste Temperatur angibt, bei der er sich in normaler Atmosphäre ohne externe Zündquelle selbst entzündet"@de)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000115 pmdco:PMD_0080055 "Auto-ignition temperature is a thermodynamic quality of a substance that specifies the lowest temperature at which it spontaneously ignites in a normal atmosphere without an external ignition source"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(skos:altLabel pmdco:PMD_0080055 "Zündtemperatur"@de)
AnnotationAssertion(skos:altLabel pmdco:PMD_0080055 "spontaneous ignition temperature"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000116 pmdco:PMD_0080055 "ThermoDynamicQuality(x) ← AutoIgnitionTemperature(x)"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(skos:altLabel pmdco:PMD_0080055 "T_AIT"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(pmdco:PMD_0000060 pmdco:PMD_0080055 "true"^^xsd:boolean)
SubClassOf(pmdco:PMD_0080055 pmdco:PMD_0080005)

# Class: pmdco:PMD_0080006 (fluid dynamic quality)
# Adopted from IOF: <https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/qualities/Qualities-Physical/FluidDynamicQuality>

AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000115 pmdco:PMD_0080006 "Fluid dynamic quality characterizes a material entity's behavior or state in relation to fluidic interaction"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000115 pmdco:PMD_0080006 "Die dynamische Fluidqualität charakterisiert das Verhalten oder den Zustand einer materiellen Einheit in Bezug auf die Fluidinteraktion"@de)
AnnotationAssertion(skos:example pmdco:PMD_0080006 "The Reynolds number of flow in a pipe is a fluid dynamic quality determining laminar or turbulent regime"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(skos:altLabel pmdco:PMD_0080006 "Qualität der Strömungslehre"@de)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000116 pmdco:PMD_0080006 "PhysicalQuality(x) ← FluidDynamicQuality(x)"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label pmdco:PMD_0080006 "Strömungsqualität"@de)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label pmdco:PMD_0080006 "fluid dynamic quality"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000116 pmdco:PMD_0080006 "Necessary and sufficient conditions for 'fluid dynamic quality' have not yet been formalized. The term is defined as a specific subtype of 'physical quality'. Distinguishing criteria are domain-specific and depend on measurement conventions or source terminology not yet expressed as OWL restrictions."@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(pmdco:PMD_0000060 pmdco:PMD_0080006 "true"^^xsd:boolean)
SubClassOf(pmdco:PMD_0080006 obo:BFO_0000019)

# Class: pmdco:PMD_0080056 (Reynolds number)
# Adopted from IOF: <https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/qualities/Qualities-Physical/ReynoldsNumber>

AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000115 pmdco:PMD_0080056 "Reynolds number is a dimensionless quantity predicting fluid flow patterns, measuring the ratio between inertial and viscous forces"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000115 pmdco:PMD_0080056 "Reynolds-Zahl ist eine dimensionslose Größe zur Vorhersage von Strömungsmustern in Flüssigkeiten, die das Verhältnis zwischen Trägheits- und Viskosekräften misst"@de)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label pmdco:PMD_0080056 "Reynolds number"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label pmdco:PMD_0080056 "Reynolds-Zahl"@de)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000119 pmdco:PMD_0080056 <https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Reynolds_number>)
AnnotationAssertion(skos:example pmdco:PMD_0080056 "Flow in a 25 mm pipe at 2 m/s has a Reynolds number of about 50000, indicating turbulent regime"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000116 pmdco:PMD_0080056 "Necessary and sufficient conditions for 'Reynolds number' have not yet been formalized. The term is defined as a specific subtype of 'FluidDynamicQuality'. Distinguishing criteria are domain-specific and depend on measurement conventions or source terminology not yet expressed as OWL restrictions. The definition is adapted from: https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Reynolds_number."@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000116 pmdco:PMD_0080056 "FluidDynamicQuality(x) ← ReynoldsNumber(x)"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(pmdco:PMD_0000060 pmdco:PMD_0080056 "true"^^xsd:boolean)
SubClassOf(pmdco:PMD_0080056 pmdco:PMD_0080006)

# Class: pmdco:PMD_0080007 (radiologic quality)
# Adopted from IOF: <https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/qualities/Qualities-Physical/RadiologicQuality>

AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label pmdco:PMD_0080007 "radiologic quality"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label pmdco:PMD_0080007 "radiologische Qualität"@de)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000115 pmdco:PMD_0080007 "Radiologic quality pertains to properties or characteristics related to an entity's interaction with radiant energy"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000115 pmdco:PMD_0080007 "Radiologische Qualität bezieht sich auf die Eigenschaften oder Merkmale im Zusammenhang mit der Wechselwirkung einer Entität mit Strahlungsenergie"@de)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000116 pmdco:PMD_0080007 "Necessary and sufficient conditions for 'radiologic quality' have not yet been formalized. The term is defined as a specific subtype of 'physical quality'. Distinguishing criteria are domain-specific and depend on measurement conventions or source terminology not yet expressed as OWL restrictions."@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(skos:example pmdco:PMD_0080007 "The dose equivalent a patient receives from a chest X-ray is a radiologic quality of the examination"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000116 pmdco:PMD_0080007 "PhysicalQuality(x) ← RadiologicQuality(x)"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(pmdco:PMD_0000060 pmdco:PMD_0080007 "true"^^xsd:boolean)
SubClassOf(pmdco:PMD_0080007 obo:BFO_0000019)

# Class: pmdco:PMD_0080008 (olfactoric quality)
# Adopted from IOF: <https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/qualities/Qualities-Physical/OlfactoricQuantity>

AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000116 pmdco:PMD_0080008 "Necessary and sufficient conditions for 'olfactoric quality' have not yet been formalized. The term is defined as a specific subtype of 'physical quality'. Distinguishing criteria are domain-specific and depend on measurement conventions or source terminology not yet expressed as OWL restrictions."@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000115 pmdco:PMD_0080008 "Die olfaktorische Menge bezieht sich auf die qualitativen Eigenschaften einer materiellen Einheit, wie sie vom Duftsystem wahrgenommen werden"@de)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000115 pmdco:PMD_0080008 "Olfactoric quantity relates to a material entity's qualitative characteristics as perceived by the scent system"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(skos:example pmdco:PMD_0080008 "The pungent olfactoric quality of ammonia is detectable at concentrations above 5 ppm"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label pmdco:PMD_0080008 "olfactoric quality"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label pmdco:PMD_0080008 "olfaktorische Qualität"@de)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000116 pmdco:PMD_0080008 "PhysicalQuality(x) ← OlfactoricQuantity(x)"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(pmdco:PMD_0000060 pmdco:PMD_0080008 "true"^^xsd:boolean)
SubClassOf(pmdco:PMD_0080008 obo:BFO_0000019)

# Class: pmdco:PMD_0080057 (odor)
# Adopted from IOF: <https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/qualities/Qualities-Physical/Odor>

AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000115 pmdco:PMD_0080057 "Odor is a morphologic quality inhering in a bearer whose molecules are dispersed and perceived by an odorant receptor"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000115 pmdco:PMD_0080057 "Geruch ist eine morphologische Eigenschaft, die einem Träger innewohnt, dessen Moleküle von einem Geruchsrezeptor verteilt und wahrgenommen werden"@de)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label pmdco:PMD_0080057 "Geruch"@de)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label pmdco:PMD_0080057 "odor"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000119 pmdco:PMD_0080057 <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/PATO_0000058>)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000116 pmdco:PMD_0080057 "Necessary and sufficient conditions for 'odor' have not yet been formalized. The term is defined as a specific subtype of 'olfactoric quality'. Distinguishing criteria are domain-specific and depend on measurement conventions or source terminology not yet expressed as OWL restrictions. The definition is adapted from: http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/PATO_0000058."@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(skos:example pmdco:PMD_0080057 "The characteristic odor of acetic acid is detectable in dilute vinegar solutions"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000116 pmdco:PMD_0080057 "OlfactoricQuantity(x) ← Odor(x)"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(pmdco:PMD_0000060 pmdco:PMD_0080057 "true"^^xsd:boolean)
SubClassOf(pmdco:PMD_0080057 pmdco:PMD_0080008)

# Class: pmdco:PMD_0080058 (odorless)
# Adopted from IOF: <https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/qualities/Qualities-Physical/Odorless>

AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000119 pmdco:PMD_0080058 <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/PATO_0001208>)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label pmdco:PMD_0080058 "geruchlos"@de)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label pmdco:PMD_0080058 "odorless"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000115 pmdco:PMD_0080058 "Odorless denotes an odor quality inhering in a bearer lacking odor"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000115 pmdco:PMD_0080058 "Geruchlos bezeichnet eine Geruchsqualität, die einem geruchlosen Träger innewohnt"@de)
AnnotationAssertion(skos:example pmdco:PMD_0080058 "Distilled water is odorless under standard conditions, emitting no detectable volatile compounds"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000116 pmdco:PMD_0080058 "Odor(x) ← Odorless(x)"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000116 pmdco:PMD_0080058 "Necessary and sufficient conditions for 'odorless' have not yet been formalized. The term is defined as a specific subtype of 'odor'. Distinguishing criteria are domain-specific and depend on measurement conventions or source terminology not yet expressed as OWL restrictions. The definition is adapted from: http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/PATO_0001208."@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(pmdco:PMD_0000060 pmdco:PMD_0080058 "true"^^xsd:boolean)
SubClassOf(pmdco:PMD_0080058 pmdco:PMD_0080057)

# Class: pmdco:PMD_0080059 (odorous)
# Adopted from IOF: <https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/qualities/Qualities-Physical/Odorous>

AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000119 pmdco:PMD_0080059 <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/PATO_0001331>)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label pmdco:PMD_0080059 "odorous"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label pmdco:PMD_0080059 "riechend"@de)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000115 pmdco:PMD_0080059 "Odorous denotes an odor quality inhering in a bearer possessing odor"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000115 pmdco:PMD_0080059 "Geruchlich bezeichnet eine Geruchsqualität, die einem Geruchsträger innewohnt"@de)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000116 pmdco:PMD_0080059 "Necessary and sufficient conditions for 'odorous' have not yet been formalized. The term is defined as a specific subtype of 'odor'. Distinguishing criteria are domain-specific and depend on measurement conventions or source terminology not yet expressed as OWL restrictions. The definition is adapted from: http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/PATO_0001331."@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000116 pmdco:PMD_0080059 "Odor(x) ← Odorous(x)"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(skos:example pmdco:PMD_0080059 "Hydrogen sulfide is odorous, detectable by humans at concentrations as low as 0.5 ppb"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(pmdco:PMD_0000060 pmdco:PMD_0080059 "true"^^xsd:boolean)
SubClassOf(pmdco:PMD_0080059 pmdco:PMD_0080057)

# Class: pmdco:PMD_0080009 (dimension quality)
# Adopted from IOF: <https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/qualities/Qualities/DimensionQuality>

AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000115 pmdco:PMD_0080009 "Dimension quality is a quality of a material entity that pertains to its measurable spatial extent, such as length, area, or volume"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000115 pmdco:PMD_0080009 "Die Dimensionsqualität ist eine Qualität einer materiellen Einheit, die sich auf ihre messbare räumliche Ausdehnung bezieht, beispielsweise Länge, Fläche oder Volumen"@de)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000116 pmdco:PMD_0080009 "BFO_0000019(x) ← DimensionQuality(x)"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000116 pmdco:PMD_0080009 "Necessary and sufficient conditions for 'dimension quality' have not yet been formalized. The term is defined as a specific subtype of 'BFO_0000019'. Distinguishing criteria are domain-specific and depend on measurement conventions or source terminology not yet expressed as OWL restrictions."@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label pmdco:PMD_0080009 "Dimensionsqualität"@de)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label pmdco:PMD_0080009 "dimension quality"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(skos:example pmdco:PMD_0080009 "the wall thickness of a steel pipe is a dimension quality determining its pressure resistance"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(pmdco:PMD_0000060 pmdco:PMD_0080009 "true"^^xsd:boolean)
SubClassOf(pmdco:PMD_0080009 obo:BFO_0000019)

# Class: pmdco:PMD_0080020 (length)
# Adopted from IOF: <https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/qualities/Qualities-Physical/Length>

AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000115 pmdco:PMD_0080020 "Die Länge charakterisiert eine 1D-Ausdehnung, die dem Abstand zwischen zwei Punkten entspricht"@de)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000115 pmdco:PMD_0080020 "Length characterizes a 1-D extent equal to the distance between two points"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(skos:example pmdco:PMD_0080020 "A steel rod measures 250 mm in length between its two end faces"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000116 pmdco:PMD_0080020 "Necessary and sufficient conditions for 'length' have not yet been formalized. The term is defined as a specific subtype of 'DimensionQuality'. Distinguishing criteria are domain-specific and depend on measurement conventions or source terminology not yet expressed as OWL restrictions. The definition is adapted from: http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/PATO_0000122."@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000116 pmdco:PMD_0080020 "DimensionQuality(x) ← Length(x)"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000119 pmdco:PMD_0080020 <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/PATO_0000122>)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label pmdco:PMD_0080020 "Länge"@de)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label pmdco:PMD_0080020 "length"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(pmdco:PMD_0000060 pmdco:PMD_0080020 "true"^^xsd:boolean)
SubClassOf(pmdco:PMD_0080020 pmdco:PMD_0080009)

# Class: pmdco:PMD_0080060 (thickness)
# Adopted from IOF: <https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/qualities/Qualities-Physical/Thickness>

AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000115 pmdco:PMD_0080060 "Thickness represents the extent of an object opposing its lateral dimensions, providing a measure of depth"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000115 pmdco:PMD_0080060 "Dicke stellt das Ausmaß eines Objekts entgegen seinen seitlichen Abmessungen dar und bietet ein Maß für die Tiefe"@de)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label pmdco:PMD_0080060 "thickness"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label pmdco:PMD_0080060 "Dicke"@de)
AnnotationAssertion(skos:example pmdco:PMD_0080060 "A sheet metal blank has a thickness of 1.5 mm, verified by micrometer measurement"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000119 pmdco:PMD_0080060 <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/PATO_0000915>)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000116 pmdco:PMD_0080060 "Necessary and sufficient conditions for 'thickness' have not yet been formalized. The term is defined as a specific subtype of 'length'. Distinguishing criteria are domain-specific and depend on measurement conventions or source terminology not yet expressed as OWL restrictions. The definition is adapted from: http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/PATO_0000915."@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000116 pmdco:PMD_0080060 "Length(x) ← Thickness(x)"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(pmdco:PMD_0000060 pmdco:PMD_0080060 "true"^^xsd:boolean)
SubClassOf(pmdco:PMD_0080060 pmdco:PMD_0080020)

# Class: pmdco:PMD_0080061 (radius)
# Adopted from IOF: <https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/qualities/Qualities-Physical/Radius>

AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000115 pmdco:PMD_0080061 "Radius is a length quality equal to the distance from the center of a circle to any endpoint on the circular boundary"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000115 pmdco:PMD_0080061 "Radius ist eine Längeneigenschaft, die gleich der Entfernung vom Mittelpunkt eines Kreises zu einem beliebigen Endpunkt auf der Kreisgrenze ist"@de)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000116 pmdco:PMD_0080061 "Length(x) ← Radius(x)"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label pmdco:PMD_0080061 "Radius"@de)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label pmdco:PMD_0080061 "radius"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000116 pmdco:PMD_0080061 "Necessary and sufficient conditions for 'radius' have not yet been formalized. The term is defined as a specific subtype of 'length'. Distinguishing criteria are domain-specific and depend on measurement conventions or source terminology not yet expressed as OWL restrictions. The definition is adapted from: http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/PATO_0002390."@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000119 pmdco:PMD_0080061 <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/PATO_0002390>)
AnnotationAssertion(skos:example pmdco:PMD_0080061 "A cylindrical specimen has a radius of 5 mm, giving a cross-sectional area of 78.5 mm2"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(pmdco:PMD_0000060 pmdco:PMD_0080061 "true"^^xsd:boolean)
SubClassOf(pmdco:PMD_0080061 pmdco:PMD_0080020)

# Class: pmdco:PMD_0080062 (width)
# Adopted from IOF: <https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/qualities/Qualities-Physical/Width>

AnnotationAssertion(skos:example pmdco:PMD_0080062 "A flat tensile specimen has a width of 25 mm in the gauge section"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label pmdco:PMD_0080062 "Breite"@de)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label pmdco:PMD_0080062 "width"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000115 pmdco:PMD_0080062 "Breite beschreibt eine 1- Dimension, die von Seite zu Seite auf einem Objekt oder Raum gemessen wird und die laterale Dimension betont"@de)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000115 pmdco:PMD_0080062 "Width describes a 1-D extent measured side-to-side on an object or space, emphasizing the lateral dimension"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000116 pmdco:PMD_0080062 "Necessary and sufficient conditions for 'width' have not yet been formalized. The term is defined as a specific subtype of 'length'. Distinguishing criteria are domain-specific and depend on measurement conventions or source terminology not yet expressed as OWL restrictions. The definition is adapted from: http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/PATO_0000921."@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(skos:altLabel pmdco:PMD_0080062 "breadth"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000119 pmdco:PMD_0080062 <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/PATO_0000921>)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000116 pmdco:PMD_0080062 "Length(x) ← Width(x)"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(pmdco:PMD_0000060 pmdco:PMD_0080062 "true"^^xsd:boolean)
SubClassOf(pmdco:PMD_0080062 pmdco:PMD_0080020)

# Class: pmdco:PMD_0080063 (diameter)
# Adopted from IOF: <https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/qualities/Qualities-Physical/Diameter>

AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label pmdco:PMD_0080063 "diameter"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label pmdco:PMD_0080063 "Durchmesser"@de)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000116 pmdco:PMD_0080063 "Necessary and sufficient conditions for 'diameter' have not yet been formalized. The term is defined as a specific subtype of 'length'. Distinguishing criteria are domain-specific and depend on measurement conventions or source terminology not yet expressed as OWL restrictions. The definition is adapted from: http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/PATO_0001334."@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000115 pmdco:PMD_0080063 "Diameter is a length quality equal to any straight line segment passing through the center of a circle with endpoints on the circular boundary"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000115 pmdco:PMD_0080063 "Der Durchmesser ist eine Längenqualität, die jedem geraden Liniensegment entspricht, das durch den Mittelpunkt eines Kreises verläuft und dessen Endpunkte auf der kreisförmigen Grenze liegen"@de)
AnnotationAssertion(skos:example pmdco:PMD_0080063 "A standard M12 bolt has a nominal diameter of 12 mm"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000119 pmdco:PMD_0080063 <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/PATO_0001334>)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000116 pmdco:PMD_0080063 "Length(x) ← Diameter(x)"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(pmdco:PMD_0000060 pmdco:PMD_0080063 "true"^^xsd:boolean)
SubClassOf(pmdco:PMD_0080063 pmdco:PMD_0080020)

# Class: pmdco:PMD_0080064 (depth)
# Adopted from IOF: <https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/qualities/Qualities-Physical/Depth>

AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000119 pmdco:PMD_0080064 <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/PATO_0001595>)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000116 pmdco:PMD_0080064 "Necessary and sufficient conditions for 'depth' have not yet been formalized. The term is defined as a specific subtype of 'length'. Distinguishing criteria are domain-specific and depend on measurement conventions or source terminology not yet expressed as OWL restrictions. The definition is adapted from: http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/PATO_0001595."@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000116 pmdco:PMD_0080064 "Length(x) ← Depth(x)"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label pmdco:PMD_0080064 "Tiefe"@de)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label pmdco:PMD_0080064 "depth"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(skos:example pmdco:PMD_0080064 "The weld penetration depth is 4 mm, fully fusing both steel plates"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000115 pmdco:PMD_0080064 "Die Tiefe charakterisiert eine eindimensionale Ausdehnung, gemessen von vorne nach hinten oder nach innen, und unterscheidet sie von Breite und Länge"@de)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000115 pmdco:PMD_0080064 "Depth characterizes a 1-D extent measured from the front to the back, or inward, distinguishing it from width and length"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(pmdco:PMD_0000060 pmdco:PMD_0080064 "true"^^xsd:boolean)
SubClassOf(pmdco:PMD_0080064 pmdco:PMD_0080020)

# Class: pmdco:PMD_0080065 (wavelength)
# Adopted from IOF: <https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/qualities/Qualities-Physical/Wavelength>

AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000119 pmdco:PMD_0080065 <https://www.oxfordreference.com/display/10.1093/oi/authority.20110803121421585>)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000115 pmdco:PMD_0080065 "Wellenlänge ist die Entfernung zwischen aufeinanderfolgenden Gipfeln oder Tälern einer Welle, gleich der Wellenbewegungsgeschwindigkeit geteilt durch die Frequenz"@de)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000115 pmdco:PMD_0080065 "Wavelength is the distance between successive peaks or troughs of a wave, equal to wave speed divided by frequency"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000116 pmdco:PMD_0080065 "Necessary and sufficient conditions for 'wavelength' have not yet been formalized. The term is defined as a specific subtype of 'length'. Distinguishing criteria are domain-specific and depend on measurement conventions or source terminology not yet expressed as OWL restrictions. The definition is adapted from: https://www.oxfordreference.com/display/10.1093/oi/authority.20110803121421585."@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label pmdco:PMD_0080065 "wavelength"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label pmdco:PMD_0080065 "Wellenlänge"@de)
AnnotationAssertion(skos:example pmdco:PMD_0080065 "A green laser pointer emits light at a wavelength of 532 nm"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000116 pmdco:PMD_0080065 "Length(x) ← Wavelength(x)"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(pmdco:PMD_0000060 pmdco:PMD_0080065 "true"^^xsd:boolean)
SubClassOf(pmdco:PMD_0080065 pmdco:PMD_0080020)

# Class: pmdco:PMD_0080066 (height)
# Adopted from IOF: <https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/qualities/Qualities-Physical/Height>

AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label pmdco:PMD_0080066 "height"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label pmdco:PMD_0080066 "Höhe"@de)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000116 pmdco:PMD_0080066 "Necessary and sufficient conditions for 'height' have not yet been formalized. The term is defined as a specific subtype of 'length'. Distinguishing criteria are domain-specific and depend on measurement conventions or source terminology not yet expressed as OWL restrictions. The definition is adapted from: http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/PATO_0000119."@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(skos:example pmdco:PMD_0080066 "A steel column has a height of 3.6 m between floor and ceiling connections"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000115 pmdco:PMD_0080066 "Die Höhe ist eine eindimensionale Ausdehnungsqualität, die die vertikale Abmessung eines Objekts oder Raums beschreibt, gemessen von der Basis bis zur Spitze"@de)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000115 pmdco:PMD_0080066 "Height is a 1-D extent quality describing the vertical dimension of an object or space, measured from the base to the top"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000116 pmdco:PMD_0080066 "Length(x) ← Height(x)"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000119 pmdco:PMD_0080066 <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/PATO_0000119>)
AnnotationAssertion(pmdco:PMD_0000060 pmdco:PMD_0080066 "true"^^xsd:boolean)
SubClassOf(pmdco:PMD_0080066 pmdco:PMD_0080020)

# Class: pmdco:PMD_0080067 (perimeter)
# Adopted from IOF: <https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/qualities/Qualities-Physical/Perimeter>

AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000115 pmdco:PMD_0080067 "Perimeter measures a 1-D extent inhering in a two-dimensional bearer, representing the distance around it"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000115 pmdco:PMD_0080067 "Der Umfang misst eine eindimensionale Ausdehnung, die einem zweidimensionalen Träger innewohnt und die Entfernung um ihn herum darstellt"@de)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000119 pmdco:PMD_0080067 <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/PATO_0001711>)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label pmdco:PMD_0080067 "perimeter"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label pmdco:PMD_0080067 "Umfang"@de)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000116 pmdco:PMD_0080067 "Length(x) ← Perimeter(x)"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000116 pmdco:PMD_0080067 "Necessary and sufficient conditions for 'perimeter' have not yet been formalized. The term is defined as a specific subtype of 'length'. Distinguishing criteria are domain-specific and depend on measurement conventions or source terminology not yet expressed as OWL restrictions. The definition is adapted from: http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/PATO_0001711."@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(skos:example pmdco:PMD_0080067 "The perimeter of a square cross-section beam of 50 mm side length is 200 mm"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(pmdco:PMD_0000060 pmdco:PMD_0080067 "true"^^xsd:boolean)
SubClassOf(pmdco:PMD_0080067 pmdco:PMD_0080020)

# Class: pmdco:PMD_0080068 (circumference)
# Adopted from IOF: <https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/qualities/Qualities-Physical/Circumference>

AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000119 pmdco:PMD_0080068 <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/PATO_0001648>)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label pmdco:PMD_0080068 "circumference"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label pmdco:PMD_0080068 "Kreisumfang"@de)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000115 pmdco:PMD_0080068 "Circumference characterizes a 1-D extent equal to the length of the closed curve of a circle"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000115 pmdco:PMD_0080068 "Der Umfang charakterisiert eine eindimensionale Ausdehnung, die der Länge der geschlossenen Kurve eines Kreises entspricht"@de)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000116 pmdco:PMD_0080068 "Necessary and sufficient conditions for 'circumference' have not yet been formalized. The term is defined as a specific subtype of 'perimeter'. Distinguishing criteria are domain-specific and depend on measurement conventions or source terminology not yet expressed as OWL restrictions. The definition is adapted from: http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/PATO_0001648."@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000116 pmdco:PMD_0080068 "Perimeter(x) ← Circumference(x)"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(skos:example pmdco:PMD_0080068 "A wire of 2 mm diameter has a circumference of 6.28 mm"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(pmdco:PMD_0000060 pmdco:PMD_0080068 "true"^^xsd:boolean)
SubClassOf(pmdco:PMD_0080068 pmdco:PMD_0080067)

# Class: pmdco:PMD_0080019 (area)
# Adopted from IOF: <https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/qualities/Qualities-Physical/Area>

AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000115 pmdco:PMD_0080019 "Area signifies a 2-D extent quality inhering by virtue of the bearer's two-dimensional extent"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000115 pmdco:PMD_0080019 "Fläche bedeutet eine zweidimensionale Ausdehnungsqualität, die aufgrund der zweidimensionalen Ausdehnung des Trägers inhärent ist"@de)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000116 pmdco:PMD_0080019 "DimensionQuality(x) ← Area(x)"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000116 pmdco:PMD_0080019 "Necessary and sufficient conditions for 'area' have not yet been formalized. The term is defined as a specific subtype of 'DimensionQuality'. Distinguishing criteria are domain-specific and depend on measurement conventions or source terminology not yet expressed as OWL restrictions. The definition is adapted from: http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/PATO_0001323."@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label pmdco:PMD_0080019 "area"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label pmdco:PMD_0080019 "Fläche"@de)
AnnotationAssertion(skos:example pmdco:PMD_0080019 "The cross-sectional area of a tensile specimen at the gauge section is 50 mm2"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000119 pmdco:PMD_0080019 <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/PATO_0001323>)
AnnotationAssertion(pmdco:PMD_0000060 pmdco:PMD_0080019 "true"^^xsd:boolean)
SubClassOf(pmdco:PMD_0080019 pmdco:PMD_0080009)

# Class: pmdco:PMD_0080018 (volume)
# Adopted from IOF: <https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/qualities/Qualities-Physical/Volume>

AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label pmdco:PMD_0080018 "Volumen"@de)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label pmdco:PMD_0080018 "volume"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(skos:example pmdco:PMD_0080018 "A cylindrical billet has a volume of 0.002 m3, determined from its radius and height"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000115 pmdco:PMD_0080018 "Volume signifies the 3-D extent quality inhering due to the bearer's occupied space"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000115 pmdco:PMD_0080018 "Volumen bezeichnet die 3-D-Ausdehnungsqualität, die aufgrund des vom Träger besetzten Raums entsteht"@de)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000116 pmdco:PMD_0080018 "DimensionQuality(x) ← Volume(x)"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000119 pmdco:PMD_0080018 <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/PATO_0000918>)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000116 pmdco:PMD_0080018 "Necessary and sufficient conditions for 'volume' have not yet been formalized. The term is defined as a specific subtype of 'DimensionQuality'. Distinguishing criteria are domain-specific and depend on measurement conventions or source terminology not yet expressed as OWL restrictions. The definition is adapted from: http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/PATO_0000918."@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(pmdco:PMD_0000060 pmdco:PMD_0080018 "true"^^xsd:boolean)
SubClassOf(pmdco:PMD_0080018 pmdco:PMD_0080009)

# Class: pmdco:PMD_0080010 (spatial relational quality)
# Adopted from IOF: <https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/qualities/Qualities/SpatialRelationalQuality>

AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label pmdco:PMD_0080010 "räumliche Relationsqualität"@de)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label pmdco:PMD_0080010 "spatial relational quality"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000115 pmdco:PMD_0080010 "Spatial relational quality is a quality that inheres in a material entity by virtue of its spatial relationship to one or more other entities, such as position, orientation, or distance"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000115 pmdco:PMD_0080010 "Räumliche Beziehungsqualität ist eine Qualität, die einer materiellen Entität aufgrund ihrer räumlichen Beziehung zu einer oder mehreren anderen Entitäten, wie z. B. Position, Ausrichtung oder Entfernung, innewohnt"@de)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000116 pmdco:PMD_0080010 "Necessary and sufficient conditions for 'spatial relational quality' have not yet been formalized. The term is defined as a specific subtype of 'BFO_0000145'. Distinguishing criteria are domain-specific and depend on measurement conventions or source terminology not yet expressed as OWL restrictions."@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000116 pmdco:PMD_0080010 "BFO_0000145(x) ← SpatialRelationalQuality(x)"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(skos:example pmdco:PMD_0080010 "the distance between a bolt and the nearest edge of a steel plate is a spatial relational quality of the bolt"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(pmdco:PMD_0000060 pmdco:PMD_0080010 "true"^^xsd:boolean)
SubClassOf(pmdco:PMD_0080010 obo:BFO_0000145)

# Class: pmdco:PMD_0080069 (physical relational quality)
# Adopted from IOF: <https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/qualities/Qualities-Physical/PhysicalRelationalQuality>

AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000116 pmdco:PMD_0080069 "BFO_0000145(x) ← PhysicalRelationalQuality(x)"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label pmdco:PMD_0080069 "physisch relative Qualität"@de)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label pmdco:PMD_0080069 "physical relational quality"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(skos:example pmdco:PMD_0080069 "The coefficient of friction between two surfaces is a physical relational quality inhering in both contacting materials"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000116 pmdco:PMD_0080069 "Necessary and sufficient conditions for 'physical relational quality' have not yet been formalized. The term is defined as a specific subtype of 'BFO_0000145'. Distinguishing criteria are domain-specific and depend on measurement conventions or source terminology not yet expressed as OWL restrictions."@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000115 pmdco:PMD_0080069 "Die physische Beziehungsqualität bezieht sich auf Eigenschaften oder Merkmale einer Entität, die von ihrer Beziehung zu anderen Entitäten abhängig sind"@de)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000115 pmdco:PMD_0080069 "Physical relational quality pertains to properties or characteristics of an entity dependent on its relation to other entities"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(pmdco:PMD_0000060 pmdco:PMD_0080069 "true"^^xsd:boolean)
SubClassOf(pmdco:PMD_0080069 obo:BFO_0000145)

# Class: pmdco:PMD_0080070 (physical rate quality)
# Adopted from IOF: <https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/qualities/Qualities-Physical/PhysicalRateQuality>

AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000116 pmdco:PMD_0080070 "Necessary and sufficient conditions for 'physical rate quality' have not yet been formalized. The term is defined as a specific subtype of 'physical relational quality'. Distinguishing criteria are domain-specific and depend on measurement conventions or source terminology not yet expressed as OWL restrictions."@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000115 pmdco:PMD_0080070 "Die physikalische Geschwindigkeitsqualität bezeichnet den Quotienten zweier physikalischer Größen in unterschiedlichen Einheiten, der die Änderungsrate einer Größe im Verhältnis zu einer anderen darstellt"@de)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000115 pmdco:PMD_0080070 "Physical rate quality denotes the quotient of two physical quantities in different units, representing one quantity's rate of change in relation to another"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(skos:example pmdco:PMD_0080070 "The rate of thermal expansion of a metal rod during quenching is a physical rate quality"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000116 pmdco:PMD_0080070 "PhysicalRelationalQuality(x) ← PhysicalRateQuality(x)"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label pmdco:PMD_0080070 "physische Geschwindigkeitsqualität"@de)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label pmdco:PMD_0080070 "physical rate quality"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000116 pmdco:PMD_0080070 "Rate =(def.) a measure, quantity, or frequency, typically one measured against some other quantity or measure"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(pmdco:PMD_0000060 pmdco:PMD_0080070 "true"^^xsd:boolean)
SubClassOf(pmdco:PMD_0080070 pmdco:PMD_0080069)

# Class: pmdco:PMD_0080071 (emissivity)
# Adopted from IOF: <https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/qualities/Qualities-Physical/Emissivity>

AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label pmdco:PMD_0080071 "emissivity"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label pmdco:PMD_0080071 "Emissionsgrad"@de)
AnnotationAssertion(skos:altLabel pmdco:PMD_0080071 "Emissivität"@de)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000115 pmdco:PMD_0080071 "Emissionsgrad ist eine physikalische Ratenqualität einer Materialoberfläche, die das Verhältnis der von der Oberfläche emittierten Wärmestrahlung zu der eines idealen schwarzen Körpers bei gleicher Temperatur ausdrückt"@de)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000115 pmdco:PMD_0080071 "Emissivity is a physical rate quality of a material surface that expresses the ratio of thermal radiation emitted by the surface to that emitted by a perfect blackbody at the same temperature"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000116 pmdco:PMD_0080071 "Necessary and sufficient conditions for 'emissivity' have not yet been formalized. The term is defined as a specific subtype of 'physical rate quality'. Distinguishing criteria are domain-specific and depend on measurement conventions not yet expressed as OWL restrictions."@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(skos:altLabel pmdco:PMD_0080071 "ε"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000116 pmdco:PMD_0080071 "PhysicalRateQuality(x) ← Emissivity(x)"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(pmdco:PMD_0000060 pmdco:PMD_0080071 "true"^^xsd:boolean)
SubClassOf(pmdco:PMD_0080071 pmdco:PMD_0080070)

# Class: pmdco:PMD_0080072 (relative isotopic mass)
# Adopted from IOF: <https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/qualities/Qualities-Physical/RelativeIsotopicMass>

AnnotationAssertion(skos:example pmdco:PMD_0080072 "The relative isotopic mass of carbon-13 is 13.003 u, slightly heavier than carbon-12"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000115 pmdco:PMD_0080072 "Relative Isotopenmasse bezieht sich auf die Masse eines einzelnen Isotops im Vergleich zu 1/12 der Masse eines Kohlenstoff-12-Atoms"@de)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000115 pmdco:PMD_0080072 "Relative isotopic mass refers to the mass of a single isotope compared to 1/12 of the mass of a carbon-12 atom"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000116 pmdco:PMD_0080072 "PhysicalRateQuality(x) ← RelativeIsotopicMass(x)"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000116 pmdco:PMD_0080072 "Necessary and sufficient conditions for 'relative isotopic mass' have not yet been formalized. The term is defined as a specific subtype of 'physical rate quality'. Distinguishing criteria are domain-specific and depend on measurement conventions or source terminology not yet expressed as OWL restrictions. The definition is adapted from: https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Atomic_mass."@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label pmdco:PMD_0080072 "relative isotopic mass"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label pmdco:PMD_0080072 "relative Isotopenmasse"@de)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000119 pmdco:PMD_0080072 <https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Atomic_mass>)
AnnotationAssertion(pmdco:PMD_0000060 pmdco:PMD_0080072 "true"^^xsd:boolean)
SubClassOf(pmdco:PMD_0080072 pmdco:PMD_0080070)

# Class: pmdco:PMD_0080073 (luminous efficacy)
# Adopted from IOF: <https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/qualities/Qualities-Physical/LuminousEfficacy>

AnnotationAssertion(skos:example pmdco:PMD_0080073 "A modern LED achieves a luminous efficacy of 200 lm/W, far exceeding incandescent bulbs"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label pmdco:PMD_0080073 "Lichtausbeute"@de)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label pmdco:PMD_0080073 "luminous efficacy"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000116 pmdco:PMD_0080073 "PhysicalRateQuality(x) ← LuminousEfficacy(x)"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000119 pmdco:PMD_0080073 <https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Luminous_efficacy>)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000115 pmdco:PMD_0080073 "Die Lichtausbeute misst, wie gut eine Lichtquelle sichtbares Licht erzeugt, berechnet als Lichtstrom geteilt durch Leistung, ausgedrückt in Lumen pro Watt"@de)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000115 pmdco:PMD_0080073 "Luminous efficacy measures how well a light source produces visible light, calculated as luminous flux divided by power, expressed in lumens per watt"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000116 pmdco:PMD_0080073 "Necessary and sufficient conditions for 'luminous efficacy' have not yet been formalized. The term is defined as a specific subtype of 'physical rate quality'. Distinguishing criteria are domain-specific and depend on measurement conventions or source terminology not yet expressed as OWL restrictions. The definition is adapted from: https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Luminous_efficacy."@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(pmdco:PMD_0000060 pmdco:PMD_0080073 "true"^^xsd:boolean)
SubClassOf(pmdco:PMD_0080073 pmdco:PMD_0080070)

# Class: pmdco:PMD_0080074 (optical absorptance)
# Adopted from IOF: <https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/qualities/Qualities-Physical/OpticalAbsorptance>

AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000115 pmdco:PMD_0080074 "Die optische Absorption definiert das Verhältnis der absorbierten Strahlungsleistung zur einfallenden Strahlungsleistung und gibt Aufschluss über die Absorptionsfähigkeit eines Mediums"@de)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000115 pmdco:PMD_0080074 "Optical absorptance defines the ratio of absorbed radiant power to incident radiant power, indicating a medium's absorption capability"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label pmdco:PMD_0080074 "optical absorptance"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label pmdco:PMD_0080074 "optische Absorption"@de)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000116 pmdco:PMD_0080074 "PhysicalRateQuality(x) ← OpticalAbsorptance(x)"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(skos:example pmdco:PMD_0080074 "A solar absorber coating has an optical absorptance of 0.96, converting most sunlight to heat"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000116 pmdco:PMD_0080074 "Necessary and sufficient conditions for 'optical absorptance' have not yet been formalized. The term is defined as a specific subtype of 'physical rate quality'. Distinguishing criteria are domain-specific and depend on measurement conventions or source terminology not yet expressed as OWL restrictions."@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(pmdco:PMD_0000060 pmdco:PMD_0080074 "true"^^xsd:boolean)
SubClassOf(pmdco:PMD_0080074 pmdco:PMD_0080070)

# Class: pmdco:PMD_0080075 (optical transmittance)
# Adopted from IOF: <https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/qualities/Qualities-Physical/OpticalTransmittance>

AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000115 pmdco:PMD_0080075 "Optical transmittance is defined by the ratio of transmitted radiant power to incident radiant power, assessing transmission efficiency"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000115 pmdco:PMD_0080075 "Die optische Durchlässigkeit wird durch das Verhältnis der übertragenen Strahlungsleistung zur einfallenden Strahlungsleistung definiert und dient der Beurteilung der Übertragungseffizienz"@de)
AnnotationAssertion(skos:example pmdco:PMD_0080075 "A 3 mm thick soda-lime glass pane has an optical transmittance of 90 % in the visible range"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000116 pmdco:PMD_0080075 "Necessary and sufficient conditions for 'optical transmittance' have not yet been formalized. The term is defined as a specific subtype of 'physical rate quality'. Distinguishing criteria are domain-specific and depend on measurement conventions or source terminology not yet expressed as OWL restrictions."@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000116 pmdco:PMD_0080075 "PhysicalRateQuality(x) ← OpticalTransmittance(x)"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label pmdco:PMD_0080075 "optische Transmittance"@de)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label pmdco:PMD_0080075 "optical transmittance"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(pmdco:PMD_0000060 pmdco:PMD_0080075 "true"^^xsd:boolean)
SubClassOf(pmdco:PMD_0080075 pmdco:PMD_0080070)

# Class: pmdco:PMD_0080076 (mass diffusivity)
# Adopted from IOF: <https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/qualities/Qualities-Physical/MassDiffusivity>

AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label pmdco:PMD_0080076 "Massendiffusivität"@de)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label pmdco:PMD_0080076 "mass diffusivity"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000115 pmdco:PMD_0080076 "Massendiffusivität ist eine physikalische Ratenqualität eines Materials, die die Geschwindigkeit beschreibt, mit der eine diffundierende Substanz pro Konzentrationsgradienten durch das Material transportiert wird, gemäß dem ersten Fickschen Gesetz"@de)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000115 pmdco:PMD_0080076 "Mass diffusivity is a physical rate quality of a material that quantifies the rate at which a diffusing substance moves through it per unit concentration gradient, as described by Fick's first law"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000116 pmdco:PMD_0080076 "PhysicalRateQuality(x) ← MassDiffusivity(x)"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(skos:altLabel pmdco:PMD_0080076 "Diffusionskoeffizient"@de)
AnnotationAssertion(skos:altLabel pmdco:PMD_0080076 "diffusion coefficient"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000116 pmdco:PMD_0080076 "Necessary and sufficient conditions for 'mass diffusivity' have not yet been formalized. The term is defined as a specific subtype of 'physical rate quality'. Distinguishing criteria are domain-specific and depend on measurement conventions not yet expressed as OWL restrictions."@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(skos:altLabel pmdco:PMD_0080076 "D"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(pmdco:PMD_0000060 pmdco:PMD_0080076 "true"^^xsd:boolean)
SubClassOf(pmdco:PMD_0080076 pmdco:PMD_0080070)

# Class: pmdco:PMD_0080077 (optical reflectance)
# Adopted from IOF: <https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/qualities/Qualities-Physical/OpticalReflectance>

AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000116 pmdco:PMD_0080077 "Necessary and sufficient conditions for 'optical reflectance' have not yet been formalized. The term is defined as a specific subtype of 'physical rate quality'. Distinguishing criteria are domain-specific and depend on measurement conventions or source terminology not yet expressed as OWL restrictions."@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000115 pmdco:PMD_0080077 "Der optische Reflexionsgrad wird durch das Verhältnis der reflektierten Strahlungsleistung zur einfallenden Strahlungsleistung definiert und bewertet die Reflexionsfähigkeit"@de)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000115 pmdco:PMD_0080077 "Optical reflectance is defined by the ratio of reflected radiant power to incident radiant power, assessing reflective capacity"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(skos:example pmdco:PMD_0080077 "A silver mirror has an optical reflectance of 98 % at 600 nm wavelength"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000116 pmdco:PMD_0080077 "PhysicalRateQuality(x) ← OpticalReflectance(x)"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label pmdco:PMD_0080077 "optical reflectance"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label pmdco:PMD_0080077 "optische Reflexion"@de)
AnnotationAssertion(pmdco:PMD_0000060 pmdco:PMD_0080077 "true"^^xsd:boolean)
SubClassOf(pmdco:PMD_0080077 pmdco:PMD_0080070)

# Class: pmdco:PMD_0080078 (electromotive force)
# Adopted from IOF: <https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/qualities/Qualities-Physical/ElectromotiveForce>

AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000119 pmdco:PMD_0080078 <https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Electromotive_force>)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label pmdco:PMD_0080078 "electromotive force"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label pmdco:PMD_0080078 "Quellenspannung"@de)
AnnotationAssertion(skos:example pmdco:PMD_0080078 "A standard zinc-copper galvanic cell produces an electromotive force of 1.1 V"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000116 pmdco:PMD_0080078 "Necessary and sufficient conditions for 'electromotive force' have not yet been formalized. The term is defined as a specific subtype of 'physical rate quality'. Distinguishing criteria are domain-specific and depend on measurement conventions or source terminology not yet expressed as OWL restrictions. The definition is adapted from: https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Electromotive_force."@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000116 pmdco:PMD_0080078 "PhysicalRateQuality(x) ← ElectromotiveForce(x)"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000115 pmdco:PMD_0080078 "Electromotive force refers to energy transferred to an electric circuit per unit charge, measured in volts, produced by transducers converting forms of energy to electrical energy"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000115 pmdco:PMD_0080078 "Unter elektromotorischer Kraft versteht man die Energie, die pro Ladungseinheit auf einen Stromkreis übertragen wird. Sie wird in Volt gemessen und von Wandlern erzeugt, die Energieformen in elektrische Energie umwandeln"@de)
AnnotationAssertion(skos:altLabel pmdco:PMD_0080078 "EMP"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(pmdco:PMD_0000060 pmdco:PMD_0080078 "true"^^xsd:boolean)
SubClassOf(pmdco:PMD_0080078 pmdco:PMD_0080070)

# Class: pmdco:PMD_0080079 (humidity)
# Adopted from IOF: <https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/qualities/Qualities-Physical/Humidity>

AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label pmdco:PMD_0080079 "humidity"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label pmdco:PMD_0080079 "Feuchtigkeit"@de)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000115 pmdco:PMD_0080079 "Humidity characterizes air's partial pressure exerted by water vapor content, defined as the mass of water to volume of the medium-water mixture"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000115 pmdco:PMD_0080079 "Die Luftfeuchtigkeit charakterisiert den Partialdruck der Luft, der durch den Wasserdampfgehalt entsteht, definiert als das Verhältnis von Wassermasse zu Volumen des Medium-Wasser-Gemisches"@de)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000116 pmdco:PMD_0080079 "Necessary and sufficient conditions for 'humidity' have not yet been formalized. The term is defined as a specific subtype of 'physical rate quality'. Distinguishing criteria are domain-specific and depend on measurement conventions or source terminology not yet expressed as OWL restrictions."@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(skos:example pmdco:PMD_0080079 "A drying oven maintains relative humidity below 5 % to prevent moisture absorption in polymer samples"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000116 pmdco:PMD_0080079 "PhysicalRateQuality(x) ← Humidity(x)"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(pmdco:PMD_0000060 pmdco:PMD_0080079 "true"^^xsd:boolean)
SubClassOf(pmdco:PMD_0080079 pmdco:PMD_0080070)

# Class: pmdco:PMD_0080080 (thermal diffusivity)
# Adopted from IOF: <https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/qualities/Qualities-Physical/ThermalDiffusivity>

AnnotationAssertion(skos:altLabel pmdco:PMD_0080080 "α"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(skos:altLabel pmdco:PMD_0080080 "Thermische Diffusivität"@de)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000116 pmdco:PMD_0080080 "PhysicalRateQuality(x) ← ThermalDiffusivity(x)"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label pmdco:PMD_0080080 "Temperaturleitfähigkeit"@de)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label pmdco:PMD_0080080 "thermal diffusivity"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000115 pmdco:PMD_0080080 "Thermal diffusivity is a physical rate quality of a material that quantifies the rate at which thermal energy is conducted relative to its capacity to store heat, expressed as the ratio of thermal conductivity to the product of density and specific heat capacity"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000115 pmdco:PMD_0080080 "Temperaturleitfähigkeit ist eine physikalische Ratenqualität eines Materials, die die Geschwindigkeit beschreibt, mit der Wärmeenergie im Verhältnis zur Wärmespeicherkapazität geleitet wird, ausgedrückt als Verhältnis der Wärmeleitfähigkeit zum Produkt aus Dichte und spezifischer Wärmekapazität"@de)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000116 pmdco:PMD_0080080 "Necessary and sufficient conditions for 'thermal diffusivity' have not yet been formalized. Although thermal diffusivity is defined as a ratio of thermal conductivity to the product of density and specific heat capacity, a co-inherence axiom cannot uniquely identify this quality among all rate qualities of the same bearer. The term is defined as a specific subtype of 'physical rate quality'."@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(pmdco:PMD_0000060 pmdco:PMD_0080080 "true"^^xsd:boolean)
SubClassOf(pmdco:PMD_0080080 pmdco:PMD_0080070)

# Class: pmdco:PMD_0080081 (work hardening coefficient)
# Adopted from IOF: <https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/qualities/Qualities-Physical/WorkHardeningCoefficient>

AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000115 pmdco:PMD_0080081 "Verfestigungsexponent ist eine physikalische Ratenqualität eines Materials, die die Geschwindigkeit beschreibt, mit der die Fließspannung bei plastischer Verformung während der Kaltumformung zunimmt, ausgedrückt als Exponent n in der Hollomon-Potenzgesetzbeziehung"@de)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000115 pmdco:PMD_0080081 "Work hardening coefficient is a physical rate quality of a material that quantifies the rate at which flow stress increases with plastic strain during cold working, expressed as the exponent n in the Hollomon power-law relation"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000116 pmdco:PMD_0080081 "PhysicalRateQuality(x) ← WorkHardeningCoefficient(x)"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000116 pmdco:PMD_0080081 "Necessary and sufficient conditions for 'work hardening coefficient' have not yet been formalized. The term is defined as a specific subtype of 'physical rate quality'. Distinguishing criteria are domain-specific and depend on measurement conventions not yet expressed as OWL restrictions."@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label pmdco:PMD_0080081 "Verfestigungsexponent"@de)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label pmdco:PMD_0080081 "work hardening coefficient"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(skos:altLabel pmdco:PMD_0080081 "Kaltverfestigungsexponent"@de)
AnnotationAssertion(skos:altLabel pmdco:PMD_0080081 "strain hardening exponent"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(skos:altLabel pmdco:PMD_0080081 "n"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(pmdco:PMD_0000060 pmdco:PMD_0080081 "true"^^xsd:boolean)
SubClassOf(pmdco:PMD_0080081 pmdco:PMD_0080070)

# Class: pmdco:PMD_0080082 (coefficient of friction)
# Adopted from IOF: <https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/qualities/Qualities-Physical/CoefficientOfFriction>

AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000116 pmdco:PMD_0080082 "PhysicalRelationalQuality(x) ← CoefficientOfFriction(x)"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000115 pmdco:PMD_0080082 "Coefficient of friction is a dimensionless scalar quality of a pair of surfaces in contact that expresses the ratio of the friction force between them to the normal force pressing them together"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000115 pmdco:PMD_0080082 "Der Reibungskoeffizient ist eine dimensionslose skalare Qualität eines Paars in Kontakt stehender Oberflächen, die das Verhältnis der Reibungskraft zwischen ihnen zur Normalkraft ausdrückt, die sie zusammendrückt"@de)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label pmdco:PMD_0080082 "Reibungskoeffizient"@de)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label pmdco:PMD_0080082 "coefficient of friction"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(skos:altLabel pmdco:PMD_0080082 "friction coefficient"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(skos:altLabel pmdco:PMD_0080082 "Reibwert"@de)
AnnotationAssertion(skos:altLabel pmdco:PMD_0080082 "μ"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000116 pmdco:PMD_0080082 "Necessary and sufficient conditions for 'coefficient of friction' have not yet been formalized. The term is defined as a specific subtype of 'physical relational quality'. Distinguishing criteria are domain-specific and depend on measurement conventions not yet expressed as OWL restrictions."@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(pmdco:PMD_0000060 pmdco:PMD_0080082 "true"^^xsd:boolean)
SubClassOf(pmdco:PMD_0080082 pmdco:PMD_0080069)

# Class: pmdco:PMD_0080083 (inductance)
# Adopted from IOF: <https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/qualities/Qualities-Physical/Inductance>

AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000115 pmdco:PMD_0080083 "Induktivität ist die Tendenz eines elektrischen Leiters, einer Änderung des elektrischen Stroms durch elektromagnetische Induktion entgegenzuwirken und so eine elektromotorische Gegenkraft zu erzeugen"@de)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000115 pmdco:PMD_0080083 "Inductance is the tendency of an electrical conductor to oppose a change in electric current through electromagnetic induction, creating back electromotive force"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000116 pmdco:PMD_0080083 "PhysicalRelationalQuality(x) ← Inductance(x)"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000119 pmdco:PMD_0080083 <https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Inductance>)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label pmdco:PMD_0080083 "Induktion"@de)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label pmdco:PMD_0080083 "inductance"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000116 pmdco:PMD_0080083 "Necessary and sufficient conditions for 'inductance' have not yet been formalized. The term is defined as a specific subtype of 'physical relational quality'. Distinguishing criteria are domain-specific and depend on measurement conventions or source terminology not yet expressed as OWL restrictions. The definition is adapted from: https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Inductance."@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(skos:example pmdco:PMD_0080083 "A solenoid coil of 100 turns has an inductance of 1 mH, opposing rapid current changes"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(pmdco:PMD_0000060 pmdco:PMD_0080083 "true"^^xsd:boolean)
SubClassOf(pmdco:PMD_0080083 pmdco:PMD_0080069)

# Class: pmdco:PMD_0080084 (force)
# Adopted from IOF: <https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/qualities/Qualities-Physical/Force>

AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label pmdco:PMD_0080084 "force"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label pmdco:PMD_0080084 "Kraft"@de)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000116 pmdco:PMD_0080084 "Necessary and sufficient conditions for 'force' have not yet been formalized. The term is defined as a specific subtype of 'physical relational quality'. Distinguishing criteria are domain-specific and depend on measurement conventions or source terminology not yet expressed as OWL restrictions. The definition is adapted from: https://www.merriam-webster.com/dictionary/force."@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000116 pmdco:PMD_0080084 "PhysicalRelationalQuality(x) ← Force(x)"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000115 pmdco:PMD_0080084 "Force refers to an influence causing an object to change its velocity, defined mathematically as a vector quantity measured in newtons (N)"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000115 pmdco:PMD_0080084 "Kraft bezieht sich auf einen Einfluss, der dazu führt, dass ein Objekt seine Geschwindigkeit ändert, mathematisch definiert als eine Vektorgröße, die in Newton (N) gemessen wird."@de)
AnnotationAssertion(skos:example pmdco:PMD_0080084 "A 100 kg mass exerts a gravitational force of 981 N on a supporting structure at sea level"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000119 pmdco:PMD_0080084 <https://www.merriam-webster.com/dictionary/force>)
AnnotationAssertion(pmdco:PMD_0000060 pmdco:PMD_0080084 "true"^^xsd:boolean)
SubClassOf(pmdco:PMD_0080084 pmdco:PMD_0080069)

# Class: pmdco:PMD_0080085 (weight)
# Adopted from IOF: <https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/qualities/Qualities-Physical/Weight>

AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000116 pmdco:PMD_0080085 "Necessary and sufficient conditions for 'weight' have not yet been formalized. The term is defined as a specific subtype of 'force'. Distinguishing criteria are domain-specific and depend on measurement conventions or source terminology not yet expressed as OWL restrictions. The definition is adapted from: https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Weight."@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(skos:example pmdco:PMD_0080085 "A concrete block has a weight of 2.5 kN in the gravitational field at sea level"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label pmdco:PMD_0080085 "Gewicht"@de)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label pmdco:PMD_0080085 "weight"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000116 pmdco:PMD_0080085 "Force(x) ← Weight(x)"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000119 pmdco:PMD_0080085 <https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Weight>)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000115 pmdco:PMD_0080085 "In der Wissenschaft und Technik ist das Gewicht eines Objekts die Kraft, die aufgrund der Erdbeschleunigung auf das Objekt einwirkt."@de)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000115 pmdco:PMD_0080085 "In science and engineering, the weight of an object, is the force acting on the object due to acceleration of gravity."@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(pmdco:PMD_0000060 pmdco:PMD_0080085 "true"^^xsd:boolean)
SubClassOf(pmdco:PMD_0080085 pmdco:PMD_0080084)

# Class: pmdco:PMD_0080086 (friction)
# Adopted from IOF: <https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/qualities/Qualities-Physical/Friction>

AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000115 pmdco:PMD_0080086 "Friction is the force resisting the sliding or rolling of one solid object over another, arising from shear between contact regions of microscopic irregularities"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000115 pmdco:PMD_0080086 "Reibung ist die Kraft, die dem Gleiten oder Rollen eines festen Objekts über ein anderes entgegenwirkt und durch Scherung zwischen Kontaktbereichen mikroskopischer Unregelmäßigkeiten entsteht"@de)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000116 pmdco:PMD_0080086 "Force(x) ← Friction(x)"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(skos:example pmdco:PMD_0080086 "Static friction between rubber and concrete has a coefficient of about 0.6, resisting sliding motion"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000116 pmdco:PMD_0080086 "Necessary and sufficient conditions for 'friction' have not yet been formalized. The term is defined as a specific subtype of 'force'. Distinguishing criteria are domain-specific and depend on measurement conventions or source terminology not yet expressed as OWL restrictions. The definition is adapted from: https://www.britannica.com/science/friction."@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label pmdco:PMD_0080086 "Reibung"@de)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label pmdco:PMD_0080086 "friction"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000119 pmdco:PMD_0080086 <https://www.britannica.com/science/friction>)
AnnotationAssertion(pmdco:PMD_0000060 pmdco:PMD_0080086 "true"^^xsd:boolean)
SubClassOf(pmdco:PMD_0080086 pmdco:PMD_0080084)

# Class: pmdco:PMD_0080087 (thrust)
# Adopted from IOF: <https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/qualities/Qualities-Physical/Thrust>

AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000116 pmdco:PMD_0080087 "Force(x) ← Thrust(x)"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label pmdco:PMD_0080087 "thrust"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label pmdco:PMD_0080087 "Schubkraft"@de)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000115 pmdco:PMD_0080087 "Schubkraft ist eine von Newtons drittem Gesetz beschriebene Kraft, bei der Massenbeschleunigung in eine Richtung eine gleich große Kraft in die entgegengesetzte Richtung verursacht"@de)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000115 pmdco:PMD_0080087 "Thrust is a force described by Newton's third law, where mass expulsion in one direction causes an equal force in the opposite direction"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000116 pmdco:PMD_0080087 "Necessary and sufficient conditions for 'thrust' have not yet been formalized. The term is defined as a specific subtype of 'force'. Distinguishing criteria are domain-specific and depend on measurement conventions or source terminology not yet expressed as OWL restrictions. The definition is adapted from: https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Thrust."@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000119 pmdco:PMD_0080087 <https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Thrust>)
AnnotationAssertion(skos:example pmdco:PMD_0080087 "A jet engine produces 150 kN of thrust at takeoff conditions"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(pmdco:PMD_0000060 pmdco:PMD_0080087 "true"^^xsd:boolean)
SubClassOf(pmdco:PMD_0080087 pmdco:PMD_0080084)

# Class: pmdco:PMD_0080088 (dose equivalent)
# Adopted from IOF: <https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/qualities/Qualities-Physical/DoseEquivalent>

AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label pmdco:PMD_0080088 "Äquivalentdosis"@de)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label pmdco:PMD_0080088 "dose equivalent"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(skos:example pmdco:PMD_0080088 "A radiation worker receives a dose equivalent of 2 mSv per year from occupational exposure"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000116 pmdco:PMD_0080088 "Necessary and sufficient conditions for 'dose equivalent' have not yet been formalized. The term is defined as a specific subtype of 'physical relational quality'. Distinguishing criteria are domain-specific and depend on measurement conventions or source terminology not yet expressed as OWL restrictions. The definition is adapted from: https://www.nrc.gov/reading-rm/basic-ref/glossary/dose-equivalent.html."@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000119 pmdco:PMD_0080088 <https://www.nrc.gov/reading-rm/basic-ref/glossary/dose-equivalent.html>)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000115 pmdco:PMD_0080088 "Dose equivalent measures biological damage to living tissue from radiation exposure, calculated as absorbed dose multiplied by a quality factor, and expressed in rems or sieverts"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000115 pmdco:PMD_0080088 "Das Dosisäquivalent misst die biologische Schädigung lebenden Gewebes durch Strahlenexposition, berechnet als absorbierte Dosis multipliziert mit einem Qualitätsfaktor und ausgedrückt in Rems oder Sievert"@de)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000116 pmdco:PMD_0080088 "PhysicalRelationalQuality(x) ← DoseEquivalent(x)"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(pmdco:PMD_0000060 pmdco:PMD_0080088 "true"^^xsd:boolean)
SubClassOf(pmdco:PMD_0080088 pmdco:PMD_0080069)

# Class: pmdco:PMD_0080089 (radiant energy density)
# Adopted from IOF: <https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/qualities/Qualities-Physical/RadiantEnergyDensity>

AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label pmdco:PMD_0080089 "Strahlungsenergiedichte"@de)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label pmdco:PMD_0080089 "radiant energy density"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(skos:example pmdco:PMD_0080089 "The radiant energy density at the focal spot of a laser is 1 GJ/m3 during material processing"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000115 pmdco:PMD_0080089 "Radiant energy density quantifies radiant energy per unit volume"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000115 pmdco:PMD_0080089 "Strahlungsenergiedichte misst die Strahlungsenergie pro Volumeneinheit"@de)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000116 pmdco:PMD_0080089 "Necessary and sufficient conditions for 'radiant energy density' have not yet been formalized. The term is defined as a specific subtype of 'density'. Distinguishing criteria are domain-specific and depend on measurement conventions or source terminology not yet expressed as OWL restrictions. The definition is adapted from: https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Radiant_energy."@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000119 pmdco:PMD_0080089 <https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Radiant_energy>)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000116 pmdco:PMD_0080089 "Density(x) ← RadiantEnergyDensity(x)"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(pmdco:PMD_0000060 pmdco:PMD_0080089 "true"^^xsd:boolean)
SubClassOf(pmdco:PMD_0080089 pmdco:PMD_0000597)

# Class: pmdco:PMD_0080090 (number density)
# Adopted from IOF: <https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/qualities/Qualities-Physical/NumberDensity>

AnnotationAssertion(skos:example pmdco:PMD_0080090 "Austenite at 900 C has a number density of about 6e28 iron atoms per cubic meter"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000115 pmdco:PMD_0080090 "Die Zahlendichte misst die Anzahl der Objekte pro Volumen- oder Flächeneinheit"@de)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000115 pmdco:PMD_0080090 "Number density measures the number of objects per unit volume or area"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000116 pmdco:PMD_0080090 "Necessary and sufficient conditions for 'number density' have not yet been formalized. The term is defined as a specific subtype of 'density'. Distinguishing criteria are domain-specific and depend on measurement conventions or source terminology not yet expressed as OWL restrictions."@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label pmdco:PMD_0080090 "number density"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label pmdco:PMD_0080090 "Stoffmenge"@de)
AnnotationAssertion(skos:altLabel pmdco:PMD_0080090 "Number Density"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000116 pmdco:PMD_0080090 "Density(x) ← NumberDensity(x)"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(pmdco:PMD_0000060 pmdco:PMD_0080090 "true"^^xsd:boolean)
SubClassOf(pmdco:PMD_0080090 pmdco:PMD_0000597)

# Class: pmdco:PMD_0080091 (pixel density)
# Adopted from IOF: <https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/qualities/Qualities-Physical/PixelDensity>

AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000116 pmdco:PMD_0080091 "Necessary and sufficient conditions for 'pixel density' have not yet been formalized. The term is defined as a specific subtype of 'number density'. Distinguishing criteria are domain-specific and depend on measurement conventions or source terminology not yet expressed as OWL restrictions."@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000115 pmdco:PMD_0080091 "Pixeldichte beschreibt das Verhältnis zwischen der Anzahl der Pixel und der Fläche, die sie auf einer verwandten Entität einnehmen"@de)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000115 pmdco:PMD_0080091 "Pixel density describes the relationship between the number of pixels and the area they occupy on a related entity"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(skos:example pmdco:PMD_0080091 "A 4K display panel has a pixel density of 210 ppi, providing sharp text rendering"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000116 pmdco:PMD_0080091 "NumberDensity(x) ← PixelDensity(x)"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label pmdco:PMD_0080091 "pixel density"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label pmdco:PMD_0080091 "Pixeldichte"@de)
AnnotationAssertion(pmdco:PMD_0000060 pmdco:PMD_0080091 "true"^^xsd:boolean)
SubClassOf(pmdco:PMD_0080091 pmdco:PMD_0080090)

# Class: pmdco:PMD_0080092 (electric flux density)
# Adopted from IOF: <https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/qualities/Qualities-Physical/ElectricFluxDensity>

AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000119 pmdco:PMD_0080092 <https://www.britannica.com/science/electric-flux>)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000116 pmdco:PMD_0080092 "Density(x) ← ElectricFluxDensity(x)"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000116 pmdco:PMD_0080092 "Necessary and sufficient conditions for 'electric flux density' have not yet been formalized. The term is defined as a specific subtype of 'density'. Distinguishing criteria are domain-specific and depend on measurement conventions or source terminology not yet expressed as OWL restrictions. The definition is adapted from: https://www.britannica.com/science/electric-flux."@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(skos:example pmdco:PMD_0080092 "Near a charged plate, the electric flux density is 8.85e-12 C/m2 per V/m of field strength"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label pmdco:PMD_0080092 "electric flux density"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label pmdco:PMD_0080092 "elektrische Flussdichte"@de)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000115 pmdco:PMD_0080092 "Electric flux density measures the total number of electric lines of force intersecting a given area, originating on positive charges and terminating on negative charges"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000115 pmdco:PMD_0080092 "Die elektrische Flussdichte misst die Gesamtzahl der elektrischen Kraftlinien, die ein bestimmtes Gebiet schneiden, von positiven Ladungen ausgehen und bei negativen Ladungen enden"@de)
AnnotationAssertion(pmdco:PMD_0000060 pmdco:PMD_0080092 "true"^^xsd:boolean)
SubClassOf(pmdco:PMD_0080092 pmdco:PMD_0000597)

# Class: pmdco:PMD_0080093 (birefringence)
# Adopted from IOF: <https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/qualities/Qualities-Physical/Birefringence>

AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label pmdco:PMD_0080093 "Doppelbrechung"@de)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label pmdco:PMD_0080093 "birefringence"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000116 pmdco:PMD_0080093 "PhysicalRelationalQuality(x) ← Birefringence(x)"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000116 pmdco:PMD_0080093 "Necessary and sufficient conditions for 'birefringence' have not yet been formalized. The term is defined as a specific subtype of 'physical relational quality'. Distinguishing criteria are domain-specific and depend on measurement conventions not yet expressed as OWL restrictions."@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(skos:altLabel pmdco:PMD_0080093 "double refraction"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(skos:altLabel pmdco:PMD_0080093 "Zweistrahl-Brechung"@de)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000115 pmdco:PMD_0080093 "Birefringence is a physical relational quality of an optically anisotropic material that specifies the difference in refractive indices along two principal optical axes, causing incident light to split into two rays with different velocities"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000115 pmdco:PMD_0080093 "Doppelbrechung ist eine physikalische relationale Qualität eines optisch anisotropen Materials, die die Differenz der Brechungsindizes entlang zweier optischer Hauptachsen angibt und bewirkt, dass einfallendes Licht in zwei Strahlen mit unterschiedlichen Geschwindigkeiten aufgespalten wird"@de)
AnnotationAssertion(skos:altLabel pmdco:PMD_0080093 "Δn"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(pmdco:PMD_0000060 pmdco:PMD_0080093 "true"^^xsd:boolean)
SubClassOf(pmdco:PMD_0080093 pmdco:PMD_0080069)

# Class: pmdco:PMD_0080094 (stress relaxation)
# Adopted from IOF: <https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/qualities/Qualities-Physical/StressRelaxation>

AnnotationAssertion(skos:altLabel pmdco:PMD_0080094 "Relaxationsgrad"@de)
AnnotationAssertion(skos:altLabel pmdco:PMD_0080094 "relaxation ratio"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000116 pmdco:PMD_0080094 "PhysicalRelationalQuality(x) ← StressRelaxation(x)"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label pmdco:PMD_0080094 "stress relaxation"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label pmdco:PMD_0080094 "Spannungsrelaxation"@de)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000116 pmdco:PMD_0080094 "Necessary and sufficient conditions for 'stress relaxation' have not yet been formalized. The term is defined as a specific subtype of 'physical relational quality'. Distinguishing criteria are domain-specific and depend on measurement conventions not yet expressed as OWL restrictions."@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000115 pmdco:PMD_0080094 "Spannungsrelaxation ist eine physikalische relationale Qualität eines Materials, die das Verhältnis der Restspannung zur anfänglich aufgebrachten Spannung nach einem definierten Zeitintervall bei konstanter Dehnung ausdrückt und die Neigung des Materials zur internen Spannungsumverteilung über die Zeit quantifiziert"@de)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000115 pmdco:PMD_0080094 "Stress relaxation is a physical relational quality of a material that expresses the ratio of residual stress to initial applied stress after a defined time interval under constant strain, quantifying the material's tendency to internally redistribute stress over time"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(pmdco:PMD_0000060 pmdco:PMD_0080094 "true"^^xsd:boolean)
SubClassOf(pmdco:PMD_0080094 pmdco:PMD_0080069)

# Class: pmdco:PMD_0080095 (contact angle)
# Adopted from IOF: <https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/qualities/Qualities-Physical/ContactAngle>

AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000116 pmdco:PMD_0080095 "Necessary and sufficient conditions for 'contact angle' have not yet been formalized. The term is defined as a specific subtype of 'physical relational quality'. Distinguishing criteria are domain-specific and depend on measurement conventions not yet expressed as OWL restrictions."@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label pmdco:PMD_0080095 "contact angle"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label pmdco:PMD_0080095 "Kontaktwinkel"@de)
AnnotationAssertion(skos:altLabel pmdco:PMD_0080095 "wetting angle"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(skos:altLabel pmdco:PMD_0080095 "Benetzungswinkel"@de)
AnnotationAssertion(skos:example pmdco:PMD_0080095 "A hydrophobic polymer coating shows a water contact angle of 110 degrees, indicating poor wettability"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(skos:altLabel pmdco:PMD_0080095 "θ"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000116 pmdco:PMD_0080095 "PhysicalRelationalQuality(x) ← ContactAngle(x)"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000115 pmdco:PMD_0080095 "Contact angle is a physical relational quality of a solid surface that quantifies the angle formed at the three-phase contact line between a liquid droplet, the solid surface, and the surrounding gas phase, characterizing the wettability of the surface by the liquid"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000115 pmdco:PMD_0080095 "Kontaktwinkel ist eine physikalische relationale Qualität einer festen Oberfläche, die den Winkel an der Dreiphasengrenzlinie zwischen einem Flüssigkeitstropfen, der festen Oberfläche und der umgebenden Gasphase beschreibt und die Benetzbarkeit der Oberfläche durch die Flüssigkeit charakterisiert"@de)
AnnotationAssertion(pmdco:PMD_0000060 pmdco:PMD_0080095 "true"^^xsd:boolean)
SubClassOf(pmdco:PMD_0080095 pmdco:PMD_0080069)

# Class: pmdco:PMD_0080096 (material composition)
# Adopted from IOF: <https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/qualities/Qualities-Physical/MaterialComposition>

AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000116 pmdco:PMD_0080096 "PhysicalRelationalQuality(x) ← MaterialComposition(x)"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label pmdco:PMD_0080096 "material composition"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label pmdco:PMD_0080096 "Materialzusammensetzung"@de)
AnnotationAssertion(skos:example pmdco:PMD_0080096 "The material composition of 304 stainless steel includes 18 wt% Cr and 8 wt% Ni"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000115 pmdco:PMD_0080096 "Material composition describes the ratio of substances or components making up a material, considering types, proportions, and arrangements"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000115 pmdco:PMD_0080096 "Die Materialzusammensetzung beschreibt das Verhältnis von Stoffen oder Komponenten, aus denen ein Material besteht, unter Berücksichtigung von Arten, Proportionen und Anordnungen"@de)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000116 pmdco:PMD_0080096 "Necessary and sufficient conditions for 'material composition' have not yet been formalized. The term is defined as a specific subtype of 'physical relational quality'. Distinguishing criteria are domain-specific and depend on measurement conventions or source terminology not yet expressed as OWL restrictions."@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(pmdco:PMD_0000060 pmdco:PMD_0080096 "true"^^xsd:boolean)
SubClassOf(pmdco:PMD_0080096 pmdco:PMD_0080069)

# Class: pmdco:PMD_0080097 (mass ratio)
# Adopted from IOF: <https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/qualities/Qualities-Physical/MassRatio>

AnnotationAssertion(skos:example pmdco:PMD_0080097 "A fiber-reinforced composite has a fiber-to-matrix mass ratio of 60:40"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000116 pmdco:PMD_0080097 "Necessary and sufficient conditions for 'mass ratio' have not yet been formalized. The term is defined as a specific subtype of 'material composition'. Distinguishing criteria are domain-specific and depend on measurement conventions or source terminology not yet expressed as OWL restrictions."@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label pmdco:PMD_0080097 "mass ratio"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label pmdco:PMD_0080097 "Massenverhältnis"@de)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000115 pmdco:PMD_0080097 "Mass ratio denotes a relational quality expressing one mass value relative to another, typically producing a dimensionless number"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000115 pmdco:PMD_0080097 "Das Massenverhältnis bezeichnet eine relationale Qualität, die einen Massenwert im Verhältnis zu einem anderen ausdrückt und typischerweise eine dimensionslose Zahl ergibt"@de)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000116 pmdco:PMD_0080097 "MaterialComposition(x) ← MassRatio(x)"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(pmdco:PMD_0000060 pmdco:PMD_0080097 "true"^^xsd:boolean)
SubClassOf(pmdco:PMD_0080097 pmdco:PMD_0080096)

# Class: pmdco:PMD_0080098 (mass mix ratio)
# Adopted from IOF: <https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/qualities/Qualities-Physical/MassMixRatio>

AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label pmdco:PMD_0080098 "Massenmischungsverhältnis"@de)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label pmdco:PMD_0080098 "mass mix ratio"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000119 pmdco:PMD_0080098 <https://de.wikipedia.org/wiki/Massenverh%C3%A4ltnis>)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000115 pmdco:PMD_0080098 "Mass mix ratio represents the ratio of masses of two mixture components, providing a quantitative composition description"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000115 pmdco:PMD_0080098 "Das Massenmischungsverhältnis stellt das Verhältnis der Massen zweier Mischungskomponenten dar und liefert eine quantitative Beschreibung der Zusammensetzung"@de)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000116 pmdco:PMD_0080098 "Necessary and sufficient conditions for 'mass mix ratio' have not yet been formalized. The term is defined as a specific subtype of 'mass ratio'. Distinguishing criteria are domain-specific and depend on measurement conventions or source terminology not yet expressed as OWL restrictions. The definition is adapted from: https://de.wikipedia.org/wiki/Massenverh%C3%A4ltnis."@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000116 pmdco:PMD_0080098 "MassRatio(x) ← MassMixRatio(x)"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(skos:example pmdco:PMD_0080098 "A concrete mix uses a mass mix ratio of cement to aggregate of 1:4 for standard structural applications"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(pmdco:PMD_0000060 pmdco:PMD_0080098 "true"^^xsd:boolean)
SubClassOf(pmdco:PMD_0080098 pmdco:PMD_0080097)

# Class: pmdco:PMD_0080099 (dry mass)
# Adopted from IOF: <https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/qualities/Qualities-Physical/DryMass>

AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label pmdco:PMD_0080099 "Trockenmasse"@de)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label pmdco:PMD_0080099 "dry mass"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000116 pmdco:PMD_0080099 "Necessary and sufficient conditions for 'dry mass' have not yet been formalized. The term is defined as a specific subtype of 'mass ratio'. Distinguishing criteria are domain-specific and depend on measurement conventions or source terminology not yet expressed as OWL restrictions."@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000115 pmdco:PMD_0080099 "Trockenmasse bezeichnet die Masse, nachdem einem Objekt die gesamte Feuchtigkeit entzogen wurde, typischerweise durch geeignete Erhitzungsmethoden in einem Ofen"@de)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000115 pmdco:PMD_0080099 "Dry mass denotes mass after removing all humidity from an object, typically using qualified heating methods in an oven"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000116 pmdco:PMD_0080099 "MassRatio(x) ← DryMass(x)"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(skos:example pmdco:PMD_0080099 "A fiber composite sample has a dry mass of 48.5 g after 24 hours in a drying oven at 80 C"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(pmdco:PMD_0000060 pmdco:PMD_0080099 "true"^^xsd:boolean)
SubClassOf(pmdco:PMD_0080099 pmdco:PMD_0080097)

# Class: pmdco:PMD_0080100 (mass fraction)
# Adopted from IOF: <https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/qualities/Qualities-Physical/MassFraction>

AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000115 pmdco:PMD_0080100 "Der Massenanteil beschreibt den relativen Anteil einer Masse an der Gesamtmasse einer Mischung, ein gängiges quantitatives Maß"@de)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000115 pmdco:PMD_0080100 "Mass fraction describes the relative proportion of a mass to the total mass of a mixture, a common quantitative measure"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label pmdco:PMD_0080100 "Massenanteil"@de)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label pmdco:PMD_0080100 "mass fraction"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000119 pmdco:PMD_0080100 <https://de.wikipedia.org/wiki/Massenanteil>)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000116 pmdco:PMD_0080100 "Necessary and sufficient conditions for 'mass fraction' have not yet been formalized. The term is defined as a specific subtype of 'mass ratio'. Distinguishing criteria are domain-specific and depend on measurement conventions or source terminology not yet expressed as OWL restrictions. The definition is adapted from: https://de.wikipedia.org/wiki/Massenanteil."@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000116 pmdco:PMD_0080100 "MassRatio(x) ← MassFraction(x)"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(skos:example pmdco:PMD_0080100 "A binary Al-4 wt% Cu alloy has a copper mass fraction of 0.04"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(pmdco:PMD_0000060 pmdco:PMD_0080100 "true"^^xsd:boolean)
SubClassOf(pmdco:PMD_0080100 pmdco:PMD_0080097)

# Class: pmdco:PMD_0080101 (mass concentration)
# Adopted from IOF: <https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/qualities/Qualities-Physical/MassConcentration>

AnnotationAssertion(skos:example pmdco:PMD_0080101 "A saline infusion solution has a NaCl mass concentration of 9 g/L"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000119 pmdco:PMD_0080101 <https://de.wikipedia.org/wiki/Massenkonzentration>)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000115 pmdco:PMD_0080101 "Mass concentration links mass of a mixture component to the total volume in quantitative description, frequently used in solutions"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000115 pmdco:PMD_0080101 "Die Massenkonzentration verknüpft die Masse einer Mischungskomponente mit dem Gesamtvolumen in einer quantitativen Beschreibung, die häufig in Lösungen verwendet wird"@de)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000116 pmdco:PMD_0080101 "Necessary and sufficient conditions for 'mass concentration' have not yet been formalized. The term is defined as a specific subtype of 'material composition'. Distinguishing criteria are domain-specific and depend on measurement conventions or source terminology not yet expressed as OWL restrictions. The definition is adapted from: https://de.wikipedia.org/wiki/Massenkonzentration."@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000116 pmdco:PMD_0080101 "MaterialComposition(x) ← MassConcentration(x)"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label pmdco:PMD_0080101 "mass concentration"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label pmdco:PMD_0080101 "Massenkonzentration"@de)
AnnotationAssertion(pmdco:PMD_0000060 pmdco:PMD_0080101 "true"^^xsd:boolean)
SubClassOf(pmdco:PMD_0080101 pmdco:PMD_0080096)

# Class: pmdco:PMD_0080102 (volume ratio)
# Adopted from IOF: <https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/qualities/Qualities-Physical/VolumeRatio>

AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label pmdco:PMD_0080102 "Volumenverhältnis"@de)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label pmdco:PMD_0080102 "volume ratio"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(skos:example pmdco:PMD_0080102 "A foam material has a pore-to-solid volume ratio of 4:1, indicating 80 % porosity"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000115 pmdco:PMD_0080102 "Volume ratio represents a relational quality expressing one volume value relative to another, typically resulting in a dimensionless number"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000115 pmdco:PMD_0080102 "Volumenverhältnis stellt eine relationale Qualität dar, die einen Volumenwert im Verhältnis zu einem anderen ausdrückt, typischerweise resultierend in einer dimensionslosen Zahl"@de)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000116 pmdco:PMD_0080102 "Necessary and sufficient conditions for 'volume ratio' have not yet been formalized. The term is defined as a specific subtype of 'material composition'. Distinguishing criteria are domain-specific and depend on measurement conventions or source terminology not yet expressed as OWL restrictions."@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000116 pmdco:PMD_0080102 "MaterialComposition(x) ← VolumeRatio(x)"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(pmdco:PMD_0000060 pmdco:PMD_0080102 "true"^^xsd:boolean)
SubClassOf(pmdco:PMD_0080102 pmdco:PMD_0080096)

# Class: pmdco:PMD_0080103 (volume concentration)
# Adopted from IOF: <https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/qualities/Qualities-Physical/VolumeConcentration>

AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label pmdco:PMD_0080103 "Volumenkonzentration"@de)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label pmdco:PMD_0080103 "volume concentration"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000115 pmdco:PMD_0080103 "Volumenkonzentration verbindet das Volumen eines Mischbestandteils mit dem Gesamtvolumen, entscheidend für die quantitative Zusammensetzungsbeschreibung"@de)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000115 pmdco:PMD_0080103 "Volume concentration links the volume of a mixture component to the total volume, crucial for quantitative composition description"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000116 pmdco:PMD_0080103 "VolumeRatio(x) ← VolumeConcentration(x)"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000116 pmdco:PMD_0080103 "Necessary and sufficient conditions for 'volume concentration' have not yet been formalized. The term is defined as a specific subtype of 'volume ratio'. Distinguishing criteria are domain-specific and depend on measurement conventions or source terminology not yet expressed as OWL restrictions. The definition is adapted from: https://de.wikipedia.org/wiki/Volumenkonzentration."@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000119 pmdco:PMD_0080103 <https://de.wikipedia.org/wiki/Volumenkonzentration>)
AnnotationAssertion(skos:example pmdco:PMD_0080103 "A paint pigment dispersion has a TiO2 volume concentration of 20 %"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(pmdco:PMD_0000060 pmdco:PMD_0080103 "true"^^xsd:boolean)
SubClassOf(pmdco:PMD_0080103 pmdco:PMD_0080102)

# Class: pmdco:PMD_0080104 (volume fraction)
# Adopted from IOF: <https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/qualities/Qualities-Physical/VolumeFraction>

AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000115 pmdco:PMD_0080104 "Volumenanteil beschreibt das Volumen eines Mischbestandteils im Verhältnis zur Summe der Volumina aller Bestandteile"@de)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000115 pmdco:PMD_0080104 "Volume fraction describes the volume of a mixture component relative to the sum of all components' volumes"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000116 pmdco:PMD_0080104 "VolumeRatio(x) ← VolumeFraction(x)"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label pmdco:PMD_0080104 "volume fraction"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label pmdco:PMD_0080104 "Volumenanteil"@de)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000116 pmdco:PMD_0080104 "Necessary and sufficient conditions for 'volume fraction' have not yet been formalized. The term is defined as a specific subtype of 'volume ratio'. Distinguishing criteria are domain-specific and depend on measurement conventions or source terminology not yet expressed as OWL restrictions. The definition is adapted from: https://de.wikipedia.org/wiki/Volumenkonzentration."@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(skos:example pmdco:PMD_0080104 "A dual-phase steel contains a martensite volume fraction of 20 %, controlling its strength-ductility balance"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000119 pmdco:PMD_0080104 <https://de.wikipedia.org/wiki/Volumenkonzentration>)
AnnotationAssertion(pmdco:PMD_0000060 pmdco:PMD_0080104 "true"^^xsd:boolean)
SubClassOf(pmdco:PMD_0080104 pmdco:PMD_0080102)

# Class: pmdco:PMD_0080105 (volume mix ratio)
# Adopted from IOF: <https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/qualities/Qualities-Physical/VolumeMixRatio>

AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000119 pmdco:PMD_0080105 <https://de.wikipedia.org/wiki/Volumenverh%C3%A4ltnis>)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label pmdco:PMD_0080105 "Mischengehaltverhältnis"@de)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label pmdco:PMD_0080105 "volume mix ratio"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000116 pmdco:PMD_0080105 "VolumeRatio(x) ← VolumeMixRatio(x)"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000115 pmdco:PMD_0080105 "Volume mix ratio defines the ratio of volumes of two mixture components to each other"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000115 pmdco:PMD_0080105 "Mischengehaltverhältnis definiert das Verhältnis der Volumina von zwei Mischbestandteilen zueinander"@de)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000116 pmdco:PMD_0080105 "Necessary and sufficient conditions for 'volume mix ratio' have not yet been formalized. The term is defined as a specific subtype of 'volume ratio'. Distinguishing criteria are domain-specific and depend on measurement conventions or source terminology not yet expressed as OWL restrictions. The definition is adapted from: https://de.wikipedia.org/wiki/Volumenverh%C3%A4ltnis."@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(skos:example pmdco:PMD_0080105 "An epoxy adhesive is mixed in a volume mix ratio of 2:1 resin to hardener"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(pmdco:PMD_0000060 pmdco:PMD_0080105 "true"^^xsd:boolean)
SubClassOf(pmdco:PMD_0080105 pmdco:PMD_0080102)

# Class: pmdco:PMD_0080106 (piezoelectric coefficient)
# Adopted from IOF: <https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/qualities/Qualities-Physical/PiezoelectricCoefficient>

AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000115 pmdco:PMD_0080106 "Piezoelektrischer Koeffizient ist eine physikalische relationale Qualität eines Materials, die die Kopplung zwischen mechanischer Spannung und elektrischer Polarisation quantifiziert, ausgedrückt als Verhältnis der elektrischen Verschiebung zur angelegten mechanischen Spannung oder des Dehnungsanteils zum angelegten elektrischen Feld"@de)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000115 pmdco:PMD_0080106 "Piezoelectric coefficient is a physical relational quality of a material that quantifies the coupling between mechanical stress and electric polarization, expressed as the ratio of electric displacement to applied mechanical stress or the ratio of strain to applied electric field"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(skos:altLabel pmdco:PMD_0080106 "piezoelectric constant"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(skos:altLabel pmdco:PMD_0080106 "piezoelektrische Konstante"@de)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label pmdco:PMD_0080106 "piezoelectric coefficient"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label pmdco:PMD_0080106 "piezoelektrischer Koeffizient"@de)
AnnotationAssertion(skos:altLabel pmdco:PMD_0080106 "d"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000116 pmdco:PMD_0080106 "PhysicalRelationalQuality(x) ← PiezoelectricCoefficient(x)"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000116 pmdco:PMD_0080106 "Necessary and sufficient conditions for 'piezoelectric coefficient' have not yet been formalized. The term is defined as a specific subtype of 'physical relational quality'. Distinguishing criteria are domain-specific and depend on measurement conventions not yet expressed as OWL restrictions."@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(skos:example pmdco:PMD_0080106 "The d33 piezoelectric coefficient of PZT ceramics is about 400 pC/N, enabling sensitive force sensing"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(pmdco:PMD_0000060 pmdco:PMD_0080106 "true"^^xsd:boolean)
SubClassOf(pmdco:PMD_0080106 pmdco:PMD_0080069)

# Class: pmdco:PMD_0080107 (clamping pressure)
# Adopted from IOF: <https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/qualities/Qualities-Physical/ClampingPressure>

AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label pmdco:PMD_0080107 "Klemmdruck"@de)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label pmdco:PMD_0080107 "clamping pressure"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000116 pmdco:PMD_0080107 "Necessary and sufficient conditions for 'clamping pressure' have not yet been formalized. The term is defined as a specific subtype of 'pressure'. Distinguishing criteria are domain-specific and depend on measurement conventions or source terminology not yet expressed as OWL restrictions."@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000115 pmdco:PMD_0080107 "Klemmdruck ist die Eigenschaft, die als quantitativer Wert die Kraft pro Fläche beschreibt, die beim Einbau einer Probe, eines Prüfkörpers oder eines Prüfstücks aufgebracht wird, typischerweise verbunden mit einer Art von Klemm- oder Spannzubehör"@de)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000115 pmdco:PMD_0080107 "Clamping pressure describes the force per area used during the mounting process of a sample, typically involving grips or similar tools"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000116 pmdco:PMD_0080107 "Pressure(x) ← ClampingPressure(x)"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(skos:example pmdco:PMD_0080107 "A hydraulic fixture applies a clamping pressure of 5 MPa to hold a workpiece during machining"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(pmdco:PMD_0000060 pmdco:PMD_0080107 "true"^^xsd:boolean)
SubClassOf(pmdco:PMD_0080107 pmdco:PMD_0000896)

# Class: pmdco:PMD_0080108 (stress)
# Adopted from IOF: <https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/qualities/Qualities-Physical/Stress>

AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000115 pmdco:PMD_0080108 "Spannung ist die innere Kraft pro Flächeneinheit, die ein Material unter äußerer Belastung erfährt, und wird häufig als Zug-, Druck- oder Scherspannung beschrieben"@de)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000115 pmdco:PMD_0080108 "Stress is the internal force per unit area a material experiences under external load, commonly described in tensile, compressive, or shear forms"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000116 pmdco:PMD_0080108 "Necessary and sufficient conditions for 'stress' have not yet been formalized. The term is defined as a specific subtype of 'pressure'. Distinguishing criteria are domain-specific and depend on measurement conventions or source terminology not yet expressed as OWL restrictions."@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(skos:example pmdco:PMD_0080108 "A cross-section of a loaded steel column bears a compressive stress of 150 MPa"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label pmdco:PMD_0080108 "Spannung"@de)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label pmdco:PMD_0080108 "stress"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000116 pmdco:PMD_0080108 "Pressure(x) ← Stress(x)"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(pmdco:PMD_0000060 pmdco:PMD_0080108 "true"^^xsd:boolean)
SubClassOf(pmdco:PMD_0080108 pmdco:PMD_0000896)

# Class: pmdco:PMD_0080109 (engineering stress)
# Adopted from IOF: <https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/qualities/Qualities-Physical/EngineeringStress>

AnnotationAssertion(skos:example pmdco:PMD_0080109 "At yield, a steel specimen with 50 mm2 cross-section under 12.5 kN shows engineering stress of 250 MPa"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000116 pmdco:PMD_0080109 "Necessary and sufficient conditions for 'engineering stress' have not yet been formalized. The term is defined as a specific subtype of 'stress'. Distinguishing criteria are domain-specific and depend on measurement conventions or source terminology not yet expressed as OWL restrictions."@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000116 pmdco:PMD_0080109 "Stress(x) ← EngineeringStress(x)"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000115 pmdco:PMD_0080109 "Engineering stress quantifies the internal force per unit area a material experiences under load, assuming the area remains constant"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000115 pmdco:PMD_0080109 "Technische Spannung beschreibt die innere Kraft pro Fläche, die ein Material unter Last erfährt, unter der Annahme, dass die Fläche konstant bleibt"@de)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label pmdco:PMD_0080109 "technische Spannung"@de)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label pmdco:PMD_0080109 "engineering stress"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(pmdco:PMD_0000060 pmdco:PMD_0080109 "true"^^xsd:boolean)
SubClassOf(pmdco:PMD_0080109 pmdco:PMD_0080108)

# Class: pmdco:PMD_0080110 (true stress)
# Adopted from IOF: <https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/qualities/Qualities-Physical/TrueStress>

AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label pmdco:PMD_0080110 "wahre Spannung"@de)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label pmdco:PMD_0080110 "true stress"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000116 pmdco:PMD_0080110 "Necessary and sufficient conditions for 'true stress' have not yet been formalized. The term is defined as a specific subtype of 'stress'. Distinguishing criteria are domain-specific and depend on measurement conventions or source terminology not yet expressed as OWL restrictions."@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000115 pmdco:PMD_0080110 "True stress is defined using the cauchy stress tensor, relating stress to the current surface size of a volume element"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000115 pmdco:PMD_0080110 "Wahre Spannung wird unter Verwendung des Cauchy-Spannungstensors definiert und bezieht die Spannung auf die aktuelle Oberflächengröße eines Volumenelements"@de)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000116 pmdco:PMD_0080110 "Stress(x) ← TrueStress(x)"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(skos:example pmdco:PMD_0080110 "At 10 % engineering strain in a tensile test, the true stress exceeds the engineering stress by the same factor"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(pmdco:PMD_0000060 pmdco:PMD_0080110 "true"^^xsd:boolean)
SubClassOf(pmdco:PMD_0080110 pmdco:PMD_0080108)

# Class: pmdco:PMD_0080111 (creep stress)
# Adopted from IOF: <https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/qualities/Qualities-Physical/CreepStress>

AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000115 pmdco:PMD_0080111 "Unter Kriechspannung versteht man eine Belastung, die mit der Zeit auftritt, wenn eine konstante Kraft auf einen physischen Körper ausgeübt wird"@de)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000115 pmdco:PMD_0080111 "Creep stress is characterized by strain occurring with time when a constant force is applied to a physical body"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000116 pmdco:PMD_0080111 "Necessary and sufficient conditions for 'creep stress' have not yet been formalized. The term is defined as a specific subtype of 'stress'. Distinguishing criteria are domain-specific and depend on measurement conventions or source terminology not yet expressed as OWL restrictions."@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(skos:example pmdco:PMD_0080111 "A polymer gasket under a creep stress of 5 MPa at 60 C relaxes significantly over 1000 hours"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label pmdco:PMD_0080111 "Kriechspannung"@de)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label pmdco:PMD_0080111 "creep stress"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000116 pmdco:PMD_0080111 "Stress(x) ← CreepStress(x)"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(pmdco:PMD_0000060 pmdco:PMD_0080111 "true"^^xsd:boolean)
SubClassOf(pmdco:PMD_0080111 pmdco:PMD_0080108)

# Class: pmdco:PMD_0080112 (adhesion)
# Adopted from IOF: <https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/qualities/Qualities-Physical/Adhesion>

AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label pmdco:PMD_0080112 "adhesion"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label pmdco:PMD_0080112 "Adhäsion"@de)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000115 pmdco:PMD_0080112 "Adhäsion beschreibt die Fähigkeit von Substanzen, sich aneinander zu binden. Dabei handelt es sich um eine Anziehungskraft zwischen zwei in Kontakt stehenden Körpern unterschiedlicher Substanzen, die die Materialleistung in wissenschaftlichen und industriellen Kontexten beeinflusst"@de)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000115 pmdco:PMD_0080112 "Adhesion describes the ability of substances to bind to each other, involving attractive force between two bodies of different substances in contact and influencing material performance in scientific and industrial contexts"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(skos:example pmdco:PMD_0080112 "The adhesion between a paint film and a steel substrate determines its resistance to delamination"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000116 pmdco:PMD_0080112 "Pressure(x) ← Adhesion(x)"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000116 pmdco:PMD_0080112 "Necessary and sufficient conditions for 'adhesion' have not yet been formalized. The term is defined as a specific subtype of 'pressure'. Distinguishing criteria are domain-specific and depend on measurement conventions or source terminology not yet expressed as OWL restrictions."@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(pmdco:PMD_0000060 pmdco:PMD_0080112 "true"^^xsd:boolean)
SubClassOf(pmdco:PMD_0080112 pmdco:PMD_0000896)

# Class: pmdco:PMD_0080113 (surface tension)
# Adopted from IOF: <https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/qualities/Qualities-Physical/SurfaceTension>

AnnotationAssertion(skos:altLabel pmdco:PMD_0080113 "surface tension"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(skos:altLabel pmdco:PMD_0080113 "Oberflächenspannung"@de)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000115 pmdco:PMD_0080113 "Oberflächenspannung bezeichnet den Effekt innerhalb der Oberflächenschicht einer Flüssigkeit, der durch Wechselwirkungskräfte zwischen ihren Molekülen verursacht wird"@de)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000115 pmdco:PMD_0080113 "Surface tension refers to the effect within the surface layer of a liquid, caused by intermolecular forces between its molecules"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000116 pmdco:PMD_0080113 "Adhesion(x) ← SurfaceTension(x)"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(skos:altLabel pmdco:PMD_0080113 "surface stress"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(skos:example pmdco:PMD_0080113 "Water has a surface tension of 72.8 mN/m at 20 C, enabling capillary rise in fine tubes"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label pmdco:PMD_0080113 "surface tension"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label pmdco:PMD_0080113 "Oberflächenspannung"@de)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000116 pmdco:PMD_0080113 "Necessary and sufficient conditions for 'surface tension' have not yet been formalized. The term is defined as a specific subtype of 'adhesion'. Distinguishing criteria are domain-specific and depend on measurement conventions or source terminology not yet expressed as OWL restrictions."@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(pmdco:PMD_0000060 pmdco:PMD_0080113 "true"^^xsd:boolean)
SubClassOf(pmdco:PMD_0080113 pmdco:PMD_0080112)

# Class: pmdco:PMD_0080114 (refractive index)
# Adopted from IOF: <https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/qualities/Qualities-Physical/RefractiveIndex>

AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000115 pmdco:PMD_0080114 "Refractive index indicates an optical medium's light bending ability; encompassing a real and imaginary part known as the extinction coefficient"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000115 pmdco:PMD_0080114 "Brechzahl gibt die Lichtbrechungsfähigkeit eines optischen Mediums an; umfasst einen realen und einen imaginären Teil, der als Extinktionskoeffizient bekannt ist"@de)
AnnotationAssertion(skos:example pmdco:PMD_0080114 "Optical glass BK7 has a refractive index of 1.52 at 589 nm, bending light in lenses"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000116 pmdco:PMD_0080114 "Necessary and sufficient conditions for 'refractive index' have not yet been formalized. The term is defined as a specific subtype of 'physical relational quality'. Distinguishing criteria are domain-specific and depend on measurement conventions or source terminology not yet expressed as OWL restrictions. The definition is adapted from: https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Refractive_index#Complex_index_of_refraction_and_absorption."@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label pmdco:PMD_0080114 "Brechzahl"@de)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label pmdco:PMD_0080114 "refractive index"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000119 pmdco:PMD_0080114 <https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Refractive_index#Complex_index_of_refraction_and_absorption>)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000116 pmdco:PMD_0080114 "PhysicalRelationalQuality(x) ← RefractiveIndex(x)"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(pmdco:PMD_0000060 pmdco:PMD_0080114 "true"^^xsd:boolean)
SubClassOf(pmdco:PMD_0080114 pmdco:PMD_0080069)

# Class: pmdco:PMD_0080115 (extinction coefficient)
# Adopted from IOF: <https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/qualities/Qualities-Physical/ExtinctionCoefficient>

AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000115 pmdco:PMD_0080115 "Extinction coefficient, the imaginary component of the complex refractive index, indicates attenuation of electromagnetic waves through a material"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000115 pmdco:PMD_0080115 "Der Extinktionskoeffizient, die imaginäre Komponente des komplexen Brechungsindex, gibt die Dämpfung elektromagnetischer Wellen durch ein Material an"@de)
AnnotationAssertion(skos:example pmdco:PMD_0080115 "The extinction coefficient of gold at 500 nm wavelength is 1.87, characterizing strong optical absorption"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000119 pmdco:PMD_0080115 <https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Refractive_index#Complex_index_of_refraction_and_absorption>)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label pmdco:PMD_0080115 "Extinktionskoeffizient"@de)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label pmdco:PMD_0080115 "extinction coefficient"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000116 pmdco:PMD_0080115 "Necessary and sufficient conditions for 'extinction coefficient' have not yet been formalized. The term is defined as a specific subtype of 'refractive index'. Distinguishing criteria are domain-specific and depend on measurement conventions or source terminology not yet expressed as OWL restrictions. The definition is adapted from: https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Refractive_index#Complex_index_of_refraction_and_absorption."@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000116 pmdco:PMD_0080115 "RefractiveIndex(x) ← ExtinctionCoefficient(x)"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(pmdco:PMD_0000060 pmdco:PMD_0080115 "true"^^xsd:boolean)
SubClassOf(pmdco:PMD_0080115 pmdco:PMD_0080114)

# Class: pmdco:PMD_0080116 (potential)
# Adopted from IOF: <https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/qualities/Qualities-Physical/Potential>

AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000116 pmdco:PMD_0080116 "Necessary and sufficient conditions for 'potential' have not yet been formalized. The term is defined as a specific subtype of 'physical relational quality'. Distinguishing criteria are domain-specific and depend on measurement conventions or source terminology not yet expressed as OWL restrictions."@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(skos:example pmdco:PMD_0080116 "The gravitational potential at the top of a 10 m column of water corresponds to a pressure head of 98 kPa"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000115 pmdco:PMD_0080116 "Potenzial beschreibt die Fähigkeit einer Entität, Arbeit zu leisten oder sich aufgrund ihrer Position oder Konfiguration innerhalb eines Systems zu transformieren"@de)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000115 pmdco:PMD_0080116 "Potential describes the capacity of an entity to perform work or transform due to its position or configuration within a system"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label pmdco:PMD_0080116 "Potenzial"@de)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label pmdco:PMD_0080116 "potential"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000116 pmdco:PMD_0080116 "PhysicalRelationalQuality(x) ← Potential(x)"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(pmdco:PMD_0000060 pmdco:PMD_0080116 "true"^^xsd:boolean)
SubClassOf(pmdco:PMD_0080116 pmdco:PMD_0080069)

# Class: pmdco:PMD_0080117 (electric potential)
# Adopted from IOF: <https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/qualities/Qualities-Physical/ElectricPotential>

AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000115 pmdco:PMD_0080117 "Das elektrische Potenzial charakterisiert den Arbeitsaufwand, der erforderlich ist, um eine Einheitsladung von einem Referenzpunkt zu einem bestimmten Punkt gegen ein elektrisches Feld zu bewegen, typischerweise von der Erde oder einem anderen Punkt außerhalb des Einflussbereichs des Feldes"@de)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000115 pmdco:PMD_0080117 "Electric potential characterizes the amount of work needed to move a unit charge from a reference point to a specific point against an electric field, typically from Earth or any point beyond the field's influence"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(skos:altLabel pmdco:PMD_0080117 "voltage"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(skos:altLabel pmdco:PMD_0080117 "Stromspannung"@de)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label pmdco:PMD_0080117 "electric potential"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label pmdco:PMD_0080117 "elektrisches Potential"@de)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000116 pmdco:PMD_0080117 "Potential(x) ← ElectricPotential(x)"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(skos:example pmdco:PMD_0080117 "The electric potential at the positive terminal of a 9 V battery is 9 V relative to the negative terminal"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000119 pmdco:PMD_0080117 <https://www.britannica.com/science/electric-potential>)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000116 pmdco:PMD_0080117 "Necessary and sufficient conditions for 'electric potential' have not yet been formalized. The term is defined as a specific subtype of 'potential'. Distinguishing criteria are domain-specific and depend on measurement conventions or source terminology not yet expressed as OWL restrictions."@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(pmdco:PMD_0000060 pmdco:PMD_0080117 "true"^^xsd:boolean)
SubClassOf(pmdco:PMD_0080117 pmdco:PMD_0080116)

# Class: pmdco:PMD_0080118 (mass potential)
# Adopted from IOF: <https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/qualities/Qualities-Physical/MassPotential>

AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000115 pmdco:PMD_0080118 "Mass potential defines a scalar quantity describing energy stored due to a material's position, shape, or configuration"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000115 pmdco:PMD_0080118 "Das Massenpotential definiert eine skalare Größe, die die aufgrund der Position, Form oder Konfiguration eines Materials gespeicherte Energie beschreibt"@de)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label pmdco:PMD_0080118 "Massenpotential"@de)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label pmdco:PMD_0080118 "mass potential"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000116 pmdco:PMD_0080118 "Necessary and sufficient conditions for 'mass potential' have not yet been formalized. The term is defined as a specific subtype of 'potential'. Distinguishing criteria are domain-specific and depend on measurement conventions or source terminology not yet expressed as OWL restrictions."@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000116 pmdco:PMD_0080118 "Potential(x) ← MassPotential(x)"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(skos:example pmdco:PMD_0080118 "The mass potential of a raised water reservoir drives flow through a turbine at lower elevation"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(pmdco:PMD_0000060 pmdco:PMD_0080118 "true"^^xsd:boolean)
SubClassOf(pmdco:PMD_0080118 pmdco:PMD_0080116)

# Class: pmdco:PMD_0080119 (heat transfer coefficient)
# Adopted from IOF: <https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/qualities/Qualities-Physical/HeatTransferCoefficient>

AnnotationAssertion(skos:example pmdco:PMD_0080119 "A forced convection air-cooled heat sink has a heat transfer coefficient of 100 W/(m2·K)"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label pmdco:PMD_0080119 "Wärmeübergangskoeffizient"@de)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label pmdco:PMD_0080119 "heat transfer coefficient"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000116 pmdco:PMD_0080119 "PhysicalRelationalQuality(x) ← HeatTransferCoefficient(x)"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000119 pmdco:PMD_0080119 <https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Heat_transfer_coefficient>)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000115 pmdco:PMD_0080119 "Heat transfer coefficient represents the proportionality constant between heat flux and the thermodynamic driving force for heat flow, used in calculating heat transfer, typically by convection"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000115 pmdco:PMD_0080119 "Der Wärmeübertragungskoeffizient stellt die Proportionalitätskonstante zwischen dem Wärmefluss und der thermodynamischen Antriebskraft für den Wärmefluss dar und wird zur Berechnung der Wärmeübertragung, typischerweise durch Konvektion, verwendet"@de)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000116 pmdco:PMD_0080119 "Necessary and sufficient conditions for 'heat transfer coefficient' have not yet been formalized. The term is defined as a specific subtype of 'physical relational quality'. Distinguishing criteria are domain-specific and depend on measurement conventions or source terminology not yet expressed as OWL restrictions. The definition is adapted from: https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Heat_transfer_coefficient."@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(pmdco:PMD_0000060 pmdco:PMD_0080119 "true"^^xsd:boolean)
SubClassOf(pmdco:PMD_0080119 pmdco:PMD_0080069)

# Class: pmdco:PMD_0080120 (magnetic susceptibility)
# Adopted from IOF: <https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/qualities/Qualities-Physical/MagneticSusceptibility>

AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000116 pmdco:PMD_0080120 "Necessary and sufficient conditions for 'magnetic susceptibility' have not yet been formalized. Although χ = M/H is a well-defined ratio, a formal equivalence axiom would incorrectly classify any dimensionless relational quality of a magnetic bearer as magnetic susceptibility. Defined as a primitive subtype of 'physical relational quality'."@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(skos:altLabel pmdco:PMD_0080120 "χ"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label pmdco:PMD_0080120 "magnetische Suszeptibilität"@de)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label pmdco:PMD_0080120 "magnetic susceptibility"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000115 pmdco:PMD_0080120 "Magnetic susceptibility is a physical relational quality of a material that quantifies the degree to which it becomes magnetized in response to an applied magnetic field, expressed as the dimensionless ratio of magnetization to applied field intensity"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000115 pmdco:PMD_0080120 "Magnetische Suszeptibilität ist eine physikalische relationale Qualität eines Materials, die den Grad angibt, in dem es sich als Reaktion auf ein angelegtes Magnetfeld magnetisiert, ausgedrückt als dimensionsloses Verhältnis der Magnetisierung zur angelegten Feldstärke"@de)
AnnotationAssertion(skos:example pmdco:PMD_0080120 "Paramagnetic oxygen gas has a positive magnetic susceptibility of 3.73e-6 m3/mol at 20 C"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000116 pmdco:PMD_0080120 "PhysicalRelationalQuality(x) ← MagneticSusceptibility(x)"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(pmdco:PMD_0000060 pmdco:PMD_0080120 "true"^^xsd:boolean)
SubClassOf(pmdco:PMD_0080120 pmdco:PMD_0080069)

# Class: pmdco:PMD_0080121 (fluid permeability)
# Adopted from IOF: <https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/qualities/Qualities-Physical/FluidPermeability>

AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label pmdco:PMD_0080121 "fluid permeability"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label pmdco:PMD_0080121 "Fluiddurchlässigkeit"@de)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000115 pmdco:PMD_0080121 "Fluiddurchlässigkeit ist eine physikalische relationale Qualität eines porösen Materials, die seine Fähigkeit quantifiziert, Fluidfluss durch sein Porennetzwerk unter einem angelegten Druckgradienten zu ermöglichen, definiert durch das Darcy-Gesetz als Verhältnis des Fluidflusses zum Druckgradienten normiert durch die Viskosität des Fluids"@de)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000115 pmdco:PMD_0080121 "Fluid permeability is a physical relational quality of a porous material that quantifies its capacity to allow fluid flow through its pore network under an applied pressure gradient, defined by Darcy's law as the ratio of fluid flux to the pressure gradient normalized by fluid viscosity"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(skos:altLabel pmdco:PMD_0080121 "k"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000116 pmdco:PMD_0080121 "PhysicalRelationalQuality(x) ← FluidPermeability(x)"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(skos:altLabel pmdco:PMD_0080121 "Darcy permeability"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(skos:altLabel pmdco:PMD_0080121 "Durchlässigkeit"@de)
AnnotationAssertion(skos:altLabel pmdco:PMD_0080121 "hydraulic permeability"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000116 pmdco:PMD_0080121 "Necessary and sufficient conditions for 'fluid permeability' have not yet been formalized. The term is defined as a specific subtype of 'physical relational quality'. Distinguishing criteria are domain-specific and depend on measurement conventions not yet expressed as OWL restrictions."@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(skos:example pmdco:PMD_0080121 "Sandstone with a Darcy permeability of 100 mD allows significant fluid flow under pressure gradients"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(pmdco:PMD_0000060 pmdco:PMD_0080121 "true"^^xsd:boolean)
SubClassOf(pmdco:PMD_0080121 pmdco:PMD_0080069)

# Class: pmdco:PMD_0080011 (speed)
# Adopted from IOF: <https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/qualities/Qualities-Physical/Speed>

AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label pmdco:PMD_0080011 "speed"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label pmdco:PMD_0080011 "Geschwindigkeit"@de)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000116 pmdco:PMD_0080011 "PhysicalProcessCharacteristic(x) ← Speed(x)"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000116 pmdco:PMD_0080011 "Necessary and sufficient conditions for 'speed' have not yet been formalized. The term is defined as a specific subtype of 'physical process characteristic'. Distinguishing criteria are domain-specific and depend on measurement conventions or source terminology not yet expressed as OWL restrictions. The definition is adapted from: https://simple.wikipedia.org/wiki/Speed."@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(skos:example pmdco:PMD_0080011 "If a train takes 1 hour to travel 100 kilometers, it has a speed of 100 kilometers per hour (62 mph)"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000119 pmdco:PMD_0080011 <https://simple.wikipedia.org/wiki/Speed>)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000115 pmdco:PMD_0080011 "Speed describes the distance an object moves in a given amount of time, always positive"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000115 pmdco:PMD_0080011 "Geschwindigkeit beschreibt die Entfernung, die ein Objekt in einer bestimmten Zeit zurücklegt, immer positiv"@de)
AnnotationAssertion(pmdco:PMD_0000060 pmdco:PMD_0080011 "true"^^xsd:boolean)
SubClassOf(pmdco:PMD_0080011 pmdco:PMD_0000008)

# Class: pmdco:PMD_0080122 (phase velocity)
# Adopted from IOF: <https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/qualities/Qualities-Physical/PhaseVelocity>

AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000115 pmdco:PMD_0080122 "Phase velocity refers to the rate at which the phase of a wave propagates, defined as wavelength divided by time period"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000115 pmdco:PMD_0080122 "Die Phasengeschwindigkeit bezieht sich auf die Geschwindigkeit, mit der sich die Phase einer Welle ausbreitet, definiert als Wellenlänge geteilt durch die Zeitperiode"@de)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000116 pmdco:PMD_0080122 "Speed(x) ← PhaseVelocity(x)"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000116 pmdco:PMD_0080122 "Necessary and sufficient conditions for 'phase velocity' have not yet been formalized. The term is defined as a specific subtype of 'speed'. Distinguishing criteria are domain-specific and depend on measurement conventions or source terminology not yet expressed as OWL restrictions."@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label pmdco:PMD_0080122 "Phasengeschwindigkeit"@de)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label pmdco:PMD_0080122 "phase velocity"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(skos:example pmdco:PMD_0080122 "The phase velocity of a longitudinal ultrasonic wave in steel is approximately 5900 m/s"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(pmdco:PMD_0000060 pmdco:PMD_0080122 "true"^^xsd:boolean)
SubClassOf(pmdco:PMD_0080122 pmdco:PMD_0080011)

# Class: pmdco:PMD_0080123 (deformation speed)
# Adopted from IOF: <https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/qualities/Qualities-Physical/DeformationSpeed>

AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label pmdco:PMD_0080123 "deformation speed"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label pmdco:PMD_0080123 "Deformationsgeschwindigkeit"@de)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000116 pmdco:PMD_0080123 "Speed(x) ← DeformationSpeed(x)"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(skos:altLabel pmdco:PMD_0080123 "strain rate"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(skos:altLabel pmdco:PMD_0080123 "Dehnrate"@de)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000115 pmdco:PMD_0080123 "Deformation speed measures the rate at which distances of adjacent material parcels change with time near a specific point, including expansion and shear rates"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000115 pmdco:PMD_0080123 "Die Verformungsgeschwindigkeit misst die Geschwindigkeit, mit der sich die Abstände benachbarter Materialpakete in der Nähe eines bestimmten Punktes im Laufe der Zeit ändern, einschließlich Expansions- und Schergeschwindigkeiten"@de)
AnnotationAssertion(skos:example pmdco:PMD_0080123 "During high-rate forming, the deformation speed of the punch reaches 10 m/s"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000119 pmdco:PMD_0080123 <https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Strain_rate>)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000116 pmdco:PMD_0080123 "Necessary and sufficient conditions for 'deformation speed' have not yet been formalized. The term is defined as a specific subtype of 'speed'. Distinguishing criteria are domain-specific and depend on measurement conventions or source terminology not yet expressed as OWL restrictions. The definition is adapted from: https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Strain_rate."@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(pmdco:PMD_0000060 pmdco:PMD_0080123 "true"^^xsd:boolean)
SubClassOf(pmdco:PMD_0080123 pmdco:PMD_0080011)

# Class: pmdco:PMD_0080012 (electric current)
# Adopted from IOF: <https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/qualities/Qualities-Physical/ElectricCurrent>

AnnotationAssertion(skos:altLabel pmdco:PMD_0080012 "electric current"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(skos:example pmdco:PMD_0080012 "A 100 W incandescent bulb draws an electric current of about 0.43 A at 230 V"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000115 pmdco:PMD_0080012 "Elektrischer Strom ist der Fluss elektrischer Ladung pro Zeiteinheit"@de)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000115 pmdco:PMD_0080012 "Electric current is the flow of electric charge per unit time"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label pmdco:PMD_0080012 "electric current"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label pmdco:PMD_0080012 "elektrischer Strom"@de)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000116 pmdco:PMD_0080012 "PhysicalProcessCharacteristic(x) ← ElectricCurrent(x)"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000116 pmdco:PMD_0080012 "Necessary and sufficient conditions for 'electric current' have not yet been formalized. The term is defined as a specific subtype of 'physical process characteristic'. Distinguishing criteria are domain-specific and depend on measurement conventions or source terminology not yet expressed as OWL restrictions."@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(pmdco:PMD_0000060 pmdco:PMD_0080012 "true"^^xsd:boolean)
SubClassOf(pmdco:PMD_0080012 pmdco:PMD_0000008)

# Class: pmdco:PMD_0080013 (force rate)
# Adopted from IOF: <https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/qualities/Qualities-Physical/ForceRate>

AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000116 pmdco:PMD_0080013 "PhysicalProcessCharacteristic(x) ← ForceRate(x)"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000115 pmdco:PMD_0080013 "In der Physik wird der Begriff \"Ruck\" manchmal verwendet, um die Ableitung der Kraft in Bezug auf die Zeit oder die mit dem Ruck multiplizierte Masse zu bezeichnen. In der relativistischen Physik wird dieser Begriff als die zweite Ableitung des Impulses in Bezug auf die Zeit ausgedrückt, da die Masse geschwindigkeitsabhängig ist. Obwohl nicht allgemein als offizieller Begriff für diese Größe anerkannt, wird der Begriff \"Ruck\" häufig von Physikbegeisterten verwendet"@de)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000115 pmdco:PMD_0080013 "In physics, yank is sometimes used to denote the derivative of force with respect to time or mass multiplied by jerk. In relativistic physics, it is expressed as the second derivative of momentum with respect to time, because the mass is velocity-dependent. Though not universally accepted as an official term for this quantity, the term \"yank\" is commonly used among physics enthusiasts"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(skos:example pmdco:PMD_0080013 "During impact testing, the force rate on the specimen rises to 10 kN/ms within the first microsecond"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(skos:altLabel pmdco:PMD_0080013 "Ruck"@de)
AnnotationAssertion(skos:altLabel pmdco:PMD_0080013 "yank"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label pmdco:PMD_0080013 "force rate"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label pmdco:PMD_0080013 "Kraftrate"@de)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000116 pmdco:PMD_0080013 "Necessary and sufficient conditions for 'force rate' have not yet been formalized. The term is defined as a specific subtype of 'physical process characteristic'. Distinguishing criteria are domain-specific and depend on measurement conventions or source terminology not yet expressed as OWL restrictions."@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(pmdco:PMD_0000060 pmdco:PMD_0080013 "true"^^xsd:boolean)
SubClassOf(pmdco:PMD_0080013 pmdco:PMD_0000008)

# Class: pmdco:PMD_0080014 (mass flow rate)
# Adopted from IOF: <https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/qualities/Qualities-Physical/MassFlowRate>

AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label pmdco:PMD_0080014 "Massendurchsatz"@de)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label pmdco:PMD_0080014 "mass flow rate"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000119 pmdco:PMD_0080014 <https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mass_flow_rate>)
AnnotationAssertion(skos:example pmdco:PMD_0080014 "A coolant pump delivers a mass flow rate of 2 kg/s of water through a heat exchanger"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000115 pmdco:PMD_0080014 "Der Massendurchfluss quantifiziert die pro Zeiteinheit fließende Masse und wird üblicherweise in Kilogramm pro Sekunde oder Pfund pro Sekunde gemessen"@de)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000115 pmdco:PMD_0080014 "Mass flow rate quantifies the mass passing per unit time, commonly measured in kilograms per second or pounds per second"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000116 pmdco:PMD_0080014 "Necessary and sufficient conditions for 'mass flow rate' have not yet been formalized. The term is defined as a specific subtype of 'physical process characteristic'. Distinguishing criteria are domain-specific and depend on measurement conventions or source terminology not yet expressed as OWL restrictions. The definition is adapted from: https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mass_flow_rate."@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000116 pmdco:PMD_0080014 "PhysicalProcessCharacteristic(x) ← MassFlowRate(x)"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(pmdco:PMD_0000060 pmdco:PMD_0080014 "true"^^xsd:boolean)
SubClassOf(pmdco:PMD_0080014 pmdco:PMD_0020226)

# Class: pmdco:PMD_0080015 (mechanical impulse)
# Adopted from IOF: <https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/qualities/Qualities-Physical/MechanicalImpulse>

AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000116 pmdco:PMD_0080015 "Necessary and sufficient conditions for 'mechanical impulse' have not yet been formalized. The term is defined as a specific subtype of 'physical process characteristic'. Distinguishing criteria are domain-specific and depend on measurement conventions or source terminology not yet expressed as OWL restrictions. The definition is adapted from: https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Impulse_(physics)."@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000119 pmdco:PMD_0080015 <https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Impulse_(physics)>)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000116 pmdco:PMD_0080015 "PhysicalProcessCharacteristic(x) ← MechanicalImpulse(x)"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000115 pmdco:PMD_0080015 "Mechanical impulse signifies the change in momentum of an object when subjected to a force over time"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000115 pmdco:PMD_0080015 "Unter mechanischem Impuls versteht man die Änderung des Impulses eines Objekts, wenn es im Laufe der Zeit einer Kraft ausgesetzt wird"@de)
AnnotationAssertion(skos:example pmdco:PMD_0080015 "A drop weight imparts a mechanical impulse of 50 N·s to the Charpy specimen during impact"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label pmdco:PMD_0080015 "mechanical impulse"@en-US)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label pmdco:PMD_0080015 "mechanischer Impuls"@de)
AnnotationAssertion(pmdco:PMD_0000060 pmdco:PMD_0080015 "true"^^xsd:boolean)
SubClassOf(pmdco:PMD_0080015 pmdco:PMD_0000008)

# Class: pmdco:PMD_0080016 (radiant energy flux)
